00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:01,890
彼岸是天堂 第二季 第五集

2
00:00:29,090 --> 00:00:31,890
"美食厅"

3
00:00:43,900 --> 00:00:46,890
说实话 达德利先生 我什么时候迟到过?
Be honest, Mr Dudley, when have you ever known me to be late?

4
00:00:46,900 --> 00:00:49,338
我不是在查你的岗 山姆 是我的表
It's not you I'm checking on, Sam. It's me watch.

5
00:00:49,339 --> 00:00:50,890
好像停了
 Seems to have stopped.

6
00:00:50,901 --> 00:00:51,890
那就买个新的 先生
Get yourself a new one, sir.

7
00:00:51,900 --> 00:00:54,890
这块表跟了我很多年了 我要拿去修修
I've had this watch many years. I'll have it mended.

8
00:00:54,900 --> 00:00:57,890
我要是你 先生 我会配备一块璀璨的怀表
If I were you, sir, I'd want to be standing there

9
00:00:57,902 --> 00:01:00,890
每一秒都走得如你一般稳当
with a shiny new timepiece, every little tick as reliable as you are.

10
00:01:00,900 --> 00:01:03,890
也许我们该让你去推销怀表
Perhaps we should let you loose on a promotion for pocket watches.

11
00:01:03,900 --> 00:01:06,900
无上光荣 先生
That would be an honour and a privilege, sir.

12
00:01:07,900 --> 00:01:09,900
噢 有奖金么?
Oh, would there be a bonus in it?

13
00:01:11,900 --> 00:01:14,308
你怎么看? 梅尔托
What do you make of it, Myrtle?

14
00:01:14,309 --> 00:01:16,890
我怎么看? 先生?
What do I make of it, sir?

15
00:01:16,900 --> 00:01:19,286
这是个值得纪念的时刻 
A moment to cherish.

16
00:01:19,287 --> 00:01:21,890
我们华丽的美食厅的第一天
 The first day of our splendid new Food Hall.

17
00:01:21,900 --> 00:01:24,890
走过托尔盖特街的顾客们将与这些
Customers who come along Tollgate Street will be met

18
00:01:24,900 --> 00:01:27,890
珍馐佳肴见面
by all manner of culinary delights.

19
00:01:27,900 --> 00:01:29,890
你是指食物么 先生?
Do you mean food, sir?

20
00:01:29,900 --> 00:01:32,890
这栋楼荒弃了一年多
This building has stood derelict for a year and more,

21
00:01:32,900 --> 00:01:34,900
它象征着犹豫和失败
a mark of hesitation and failure.

22
00:01:35,900 --> 00:01:38,890
现在它象征着一种决心
Now it stands as a declaration of intent,

23
00:01:38,900 --> 00:01:42,536
宣告汤姆・威斯顿将一手把天堂百货
an assertion that Tom Weston means to raise The Paradise

24
00:01:42,537 --> 00:01:43,900
捧上新的高度
to new heights.

25
00:01:44,900 --> 00:01:49,890
真好 你满意我也开心 威斯顿先生
Well, I'm pleased that you're so pleased, Mr Weston, sir.

26
00:01:49,900 --> 00:01:51,900
你怎么没去工作 梅尔托?
Why aren't you at work, Myrtle?

27
00:01:53,900 --> 00:01:55,890
我做了
I was.

28
00:01:55,900 --> 00:01:56,890
我 我是说 我就做
I-I mean, I will be.

29
00:01:56,900 --> 00:01:58,090
我在工作 
I am. 

30
00:01:58,091 --> 00:02:01,900
我就是被你的慷慨陈词震住了 先生
I just got caught up in all your declarations, sir.

31
00:02:07,900 --> 00:02:08,890
分享佣金?
Share our commission?

32
00:02:08,900 --> 00:02:13,890
是的 每周结束我们大家将把佣金平分
At the end of every week we will divide the total amongst all of the girls, yes.

33
00:02:13,900 --> 00:02:16,890
为什么我们得这样? 这对那些勤勤恳恳
Why would we do that? Those of us who work hardest,

34
00:02:16,900 --> 00:02:18,890
战战兢兢伺候老主顾的人不公平
who take a care to pamper our regular customers,

35
00:02:18,900 --> 00:02:20,890
你这是把我们应得的给夺走了
you'd be taking the earnings out of our purses.

36
00:02:20,900 --> 00:02:23,308
但要是我们把佣金集中在一起 
But if we pool the money, 

37
00:02:23,309 --> 00:02:25,890
当我们中一人得病或者遭了祸事
if one of us is sick or has a run of bad luck,

38
00:02:25,900 --> 00:02:26,890
就相当有了保障
then there's a safety net.

39
00:02:26,900 --> 00:02:29,155
要是我们有为彼此工作的概念
If we feel that we're working for each other,

40
00:02:29,156 --> 00:02:30,890
相信我们会挣得更多
 then I believe we'll earn more.

41
00:02:30,900 --> 00:02:32,070
非得这样么? 
Do we have to? 

42
00:02:32,071 --> 00:02:33,890
可是苏西 你挣得最少
But Susy, you earn the least commission of all.

43
00:02:33,900 --> 00:02:36,890
即使是一星半点也是我挣的
It might be nothing but it is my nothing.

44
00:02:36,900 --> 00:02:39,890
难道不是竞争 戒备和恐惧
Isn't the competition, the jealousy and fear,

45
00:02:39,900 --> 00:02:41,890
鞭策着我们努力工作的么?
isn't that what spurs us on?

46
00:02:41,900 --> 00:02:45,900
我觉得不是非要竞争不可 我们都爱这份工作
I don't believe we have to compete. We all love our work.

47
00:02:46,900 --> 00:02:49,890
- 我建议投票表决 - 投票?
- I suggest we have a vote. - A vote?

48
00:02:49,900 --> 00:02:52,890
要是你输了呢? 那你不就威严扫地了?
What if you lose? Won't that undermine your authority?

49
00:02:52,900 --> 00:02:54,890
我不这么看 克莱拉
I don't see it that way, Clara.

50
00:02:54,900 --> 00:02:56,081
如果是妙计 总会赢得支持的
If it's a good idea, it will win.

51
00:02:56,082 --> 00:02:56,900
如果不是 就不会
 If it's not, then it won't.

52
00:02:57,900 --> 00:03:01,900
同意分享佣金的人 请举手
Raise your hand, please, if you think we should share the commission.

53
00:03:09,900 --> 00:03:11,900
谢谢
Thank you.

54
00:03:12,900 --> 00:03:14,039
这是达德利的想法
It was Dudley's suggestion.

55
00:03:14,040 --> 00:03:15,890
我们把柜台安置在醒目位置
 We've placed the counter prominently

56
00:03:15,900 --> 00:03:18,890
陈列着精美时钟吸引眼球
and stationed decorative clocks to draw the eye.

57
00:03:18,900 --> 00:03:19,890
剩下的就靠山姆的三寸不烂之舌了
The rest is in Sam's capable hands.

58
00:03:19,900 --> 00:03:22,890
关键是 让绅士们感觉没有一块怀表揣着
The point is, is to make the gentlemen feel behind the times

59
00:03:22,900 --> 00:03:24,890
就落伍了
without a little ticker in their pocket.

60
00:03:24,900 --> 00:03:26,890
这不在于他们能否买的起怀表
It's not whether they can afford it,

61
00:03:26,900 --> 00:03:29,890
而是他们能否经得住过时的恐惧感
it's whether they can afford to live of being in fear of being late.

62
00:03:29,900 --> 00:03:33,890
珠光宝气 就和我看到美食厅的感觉一样
Jewellery. Just as I have opened the Food Hall,

63
00:03:33,900 --> 00:03:35,890
你的特色明显是珠宝展
you feature a prominent display of jewellery.

64
00:03:35,900 --> 00:03:37,890
这不是装饰品 威斯顿先生
These are not ornaments, Mr Weston.

65
00:03:37,900 --> 00:03:41,890
它们是实用的东西 功能性的工具
They are practical pieces, functional instruments.

66
00:03:41,900 --> 00:03:44,900
以金银包裹 珠宝点缀的功能性工具
Functional instruments of gold and silver, decorated with jewels.

67
00:03:45,900 --> 00:03:47,040
请允许我说一句 
If I may, 

68
00:03:47,041 --> 00:03:49,890
先生 我们需要的是能让顾客神魂颠倒的东西
what we need, gentlemen, is something to fascinate the customers.

69
00:03:49,900 --> 00:03:51,890
也许是一块让人叹为观止的怀表
Perhaps, one watch for them to marvel at,

70
00:03:51,900 --> 00:03:55,890
一种奢华夺目的美 使人为之驻足  
something truly extravagant, so they will dwell long enough

71
00:03:55,900 --> 00:03:57,900
久到足够我施展浑身解数
for me to work my magic on them.

72
00:03:58,900 --> 00:04:00,890
- 克莱拉? - 嗯?
- Clara? - Mmm?

73
00:04:00,900 --> 00:04:03,900
我一直在想你为何会投票赞成分享佣金
I can't help wondering why you voted to share the commission.

74
00:04:04,900 --> 00:04:06,890
我不傻
I'm no fool.

75
00:04:06,900 --> 00:04:08,890
举手反对你 我就会输
Put me hand up against you, I'd have lost

76
00:04:08,900 --> 00:04:10,890
然后独我一个像是挑衅生事
and be left looking like a trouble-maker.

77
00:04:10,900 --> 00:04:13,890
- 我相信这不是你的理由 - 那你说呢?
- I don't believe that was your reason. - Then what was it?

78
00:04:13,900 --> 00:04:15,400
其他人都不喜欢这个提议
The other girls didn't like the notion 

79
00:04:15,401 --> 00:04:16,900
你又不想我孤立无援的
and you didn't want to leave me stranded.

80
00:04:17,900 --> 00:04:21,890
你觉得我是和事佬? 你还是不懂我 德妮丝
Think I have a heart of soap? You still don't know me, Denise.

81
00:04:21,900 --> 00:04:24,890
那就是你明白这是个妙计
Then you know it's a good idea.

82
00:04:24,900 --> 00:04:26,890
想听真话么?
Do you want the truth?

83
00:04:26,900 --> 00:04:29,900
你让我们来投票 我感激不尽
You asked us to vote. I was grateful for that.

84
00:04:30,900 --> 00:04:32,890
很好 因为我们将有下一次投票了
Good. Because we're going to have another vote.

85
00:04:32,900 --> 00:04:35,890
- 苍天啊 这次又是什么? - 不知道
- Oh, Lord! What about this time? - I don't know.

86
00:04:35,900 --> 00:04:37,608
我想让每个人轮流提个建议
I'd like each of the girls in turn to make a proposal

87
00:04:37,609 --> 00:04:38,890
然后我们投票表决
 and we'll vote on it.

88
00:04:38,900 --> 00:04:40,900
如果你第一个提出 我将不胜感激 克莱拉
I would appreciate if you would go first, Clara.

89
00:04:45,900 --> 00:04:48,110
如果你看见一个男人戴着一块精美的表
If you watch a man with a fine watch,

90
00:04:48,111 --> 00:04:48,890
你怎么看?
 what do you see?

91
00:04:48,900 --> 00:04:50,890
他是个与时间同行的人
He is a man with time on his side.

92
00:04:50,900 --> 00:04:53,890
一个不用依靠时钟的人
A man who won't be watching the clock.

93
00:04:53,900 --> 00:04:55,890
时间不等人
Time waits for no man.

94
00:04:55,900 --> 00:04:59,890
我们每周一起去游一次泳 算是女孩出游节
Once a week we go swimming together. A girl's day out.

95
00:04:59,900 --> 00:05:01,900
我们可以看着苏西沉底然后哈哈大笑
We can all watch Susy sinking and have a laugh.

96
00:05:12,900 --> 00:05:16,890
如果新开的美食厅反响不错 先生
If the new Food Hall is a success, sir,

97
00:05:16,900 --> 00:05:18,900
威斯顿扩张的胃口会增大
Mr Weston will have a taste for more expansion.

98
00:05:19,900 --> 00:05:21,890
他已经和我说了很多
He's already said as much to me.

99
00:05:21,900 --> 00:05:24,890
难不成要眼睁睁地等到难...难以企及?
Are we to wait until he is b...beyond reach?

100
00:05:24,900 --> 00:05:26,890
我们得给他们施压了
We must put more pressure on them.

101
00:05:26,900 --> 00:05:29,890
我们需要做的是让威斯顿先生
What we need, sir, is for Mr Weston to feel

102
00:05:29,900 --> 00:05:33,890
感到在这儿就是丢人现眼
that being here is a humiliation to him.

103
00:05:33,900 --> 00:05:36,900
如果他察觉出自己的妻子还喜欢你...
If he senses that his wife still favours you...

104
00:05:40,900 --> 00:05:42,890
要我做这个 鸡皮疙瘩掉一地了
It makes my skin crawl to do this.

105
00:05:42,900 --> 00:05:47,890
威斯顿太太享受特权带来的好处 不是么?
Mrs Weston enjoys all the benefits of privilege, does she not?

106
00:05:48,900 --> 00:05:51,890
你我点点滴滴日积月累到到今日
You and I have carved our lives from nothing.

107
00:05:51,900 --> 00:05:56,890
先生 这个女人夺走了你苦心经营的天堂百货
Sir. The same woman stripped you of everything you had worked for.

108
00:05:56,900 --> 00:05:58,471
同样是这个女人寸步不让
The same woman did not flinch,

109
00:05:58,472 --> 00:05:59,900
把你从这个城镇赶走
 driving you from this town.

110
00:06:00,900 --> 00:06:05,890
请你思考一下 她为何召你回来?
I ask you to consider - why does she summon you back here?

111
00:06:05,900 --> 00:06:08,900
你以为她会对你心存善意?
Do you think she is brimming with good intentions towards you?

112
00:06:09,900 --> 00:06:13,890
- 不 - 我们时间紧迫了
- No. - We have a limited time to act.

113
00:06:13,900 --> 00:06:17,890
你的思想必须集中在必须得到的东西上
You must focus your mind only on what must be achieved.

114
00:06:17,900 --> 00:06:21,890
我们需要别的什么 我们需要更多
We need something else. Something more.

115
00:06:21,900 --> 00:06:24,900
某种能够干扰汤姆・威斯顿的力量
Something to cut into Tom Weston.

116
00:06:31,900 --> 00:06:34,900
你有主意了 先生?
You have an idea in mind, sir?

117
00:06:35,900 --> 00:06:37,890
也许
Perhaps.

118
00:06:37,900 --> 00:06:40,900
是什么?
What is it?

119
00:06:41,900 --> 00:06:43,890
我还是不说的好
I'd rather not say.

120
00:06:43,900 --> 00:06:45,900
没有犹豫的功夫了
There is no room for hesitation.

121
00:06:46,900 --> 00:06:49,890
你必须去追求她 莫里
You must go after her, Moray,

122
00:06:49,900 --> 00:06:51,900
施展你的美男计
with all those charms you're famous for.

123
00:06:57,900 --> 00:07:00,890
我觉得这事我需要询问你的丈夫
I realise that this is something I need to ask your husband about,

124
00:07:00,900 --> 00:07:04,890
但是我认为需要先征求你的允许
but I felt obliged to seek your permission first

125
00:07:04,900 --> 00:07:09,890
因为这是很私人的事情 寄托着你的感情
since it's such a personal matter, such a tender issue to you.

126
00:07:09,900 --> 00:07:11,890
什么这么敏感?
What could be so sensitive?

127
00:07:11,900 --> 00:07:13,890
你父亲的怀表
Your father's watch.

128
00:07:13,900 --> 00:07:15,127
我没法控制地想 
I can't shake off the idea that

129
00:07:15,128 --> 00:07:17,890
这块怀表会成为一场展览最神奇的重头戏
 it would make the most magical centrepiece for a display...

130
00:07:17,900 --> 00:07:19,890
我父亲的怀表?
My father's watch?

131
00:07:19,900 --> 00:07:22,890
对 对 它那么的精美绝伦 会吸引...
Yes, yes, it's such a thing of beauty that it would draw...

132
00:07:22,900 --> 00:07:24,890
它对我的意义无法估量
It is precious to me beyond reckoning.

133
00:07:24,900 --> 00:07:27,890
你认为 为了吸引贩夫走卒进你的商场
Do you suppose I would dangle it before any passing drayman

134
00:07:27,900 --> 00:07:29,890
我会由它悬挂在他们面前摇摆?
in the hope that he will come into your store?

135
00:07:29,900 --> 00:07:32,890
我无意冒犯 凯瑟琳
I had no wish to cause offence, Katherine.

136
00:07:32,900 --> 00:07:35,890
可是你却口不择言
And you made no effort to exercise consideration.

137
00:07:35,900 --> 00:07:37,207
我庆幸没有去问你的丈夫... 
I'm glad that I did not ask your husband... 

138
00:07:37,208 --> 00:07:37,900
表不在汤姆手上
Tom does not have it.

139
00:07:40,900 --> 00:07:42,900
不好意思 我还以为 呃...
I'm sorry. I simply thought that, erm...

140
00:07:43,900 --> 00:07:46,890
我记得你父亲说 由于他膝下无子
I remember your father saying since he had no sons,

141
00:07:46,900 --> 00:07:48,900
他会把怀表传给你的丈夫
he would leave it to the man you married.

142
00:07:49,900 --> 00:07:51,890
是的 这个
Yes. Well.

143
00:07:51,900 --> 00:07:53,900
那是他曾经考虑过的事情
That may have been something he considered at one time.

144
00:07:57,900 --> 00:08:01,890
呃 希望你能原谅我的不善言辞 凯瑟琳
Erm... I hope you can forgive my clumsiness, Katherine,

145
00:08:01,900 --> 00:08:03,890
但是 我想要用这场展览来表示尊重...
but I intended for the display to show respect...

146
00:08:03,900 --> 00:08:06,890
如果你称呼我为威斯顿夫人 我将不胜感激
I would appreciate it if you would address me as Mrs Weston.

147
00:08:06,900 --> 00:08:08,900
当然 威斯顿夫人
Of course. Mrs Weston.

148
00:08:09,900 --> 00:08:11,900
当然
Of course.

149
00:08:17,900 --> 00:08:19,900
德妮丝 请进
Denise. Come in.

150
00:08:21,900 --> 00:08:24,890
你想要和我谈谈是么 威斯顿先生?
You wanted to speak with me, Mr Weston, sir?

151
00:08:24,900 --> 00:08:27,890
从你成为女装部主管开始 
Since you've become Head of Ladieswear there is a matter

152
00:08:27,900 --> 00:08:29,608
我越来越关心一个问题
that is of growing concern to me. 

153
00:08:29,609 --> 00:08:30,890
很抱歉 先生
I'm sorry to hear that, sir.

154
00:08:30,900 --> 00:08:33,011
似乎你引进了更多现代化
It seems you're introducing more modern, 

155
00:08:33,012 --> 00:08:35,890
或者可以称之为民主的管理方法
one might even call them democratic methods.

156
00:08:35,900 --> 00:08:38,900
- 先生 我只是... - 大开眼界
- Sir, I only want... - Most impressive.

157
00:08:40,900 --> 00:08:44,890
我关心的是为何其他的部门还不跟上
My concern is why the other departments so patently lag behind.

158
00:08:44,900 --> 00:08:48,900
我想把所有部门的主管召集起来 听你演讲
I intend to gather all the heads of department together so that you might address them.

159
00:08:49,900 --> 00:08:52,900
也许你可以用你的魔力去鼓舞他们
Perhaps you can infuse them with a touch of your magic.

160
00:08:53,900 --> 00:08:55,890
先生 我不确定我能...
Sir, I am not sure that it is my...

161
00:08:55,900 --> 00:08:58,890
怎么 你不喜欢这主意? 哪还能有更好的?
What, you don't like the idea? What could be better?

162
00:08:58,900 --> 00:09:01,890
我将得益于你的青春奔放
I will gain the benefit of your youthful ebullience

163
00:09:01,900 --> 00:09:04,890
你也将享受你应得的赞誉
and you will enjoy the recognition you deserve.

164
00:09:04,900 --> 00:09:09,890
真的 德妮丝 你可以让自己稍稍享受一下
Surely, Denise, you can let yourself bask just a little

165
00:09:09,900 --> 00:09:11,900
同事们的钦羡
in the admiration of your peers?

166
00:09:12,900 --> 00:09:14,890
- 那 我... - 很好 
- Well, I... - Good.

167
00:09:14,900 --> 00:09:16,900
我来安排
I will make the arrangements.

168
00:09:24,900 --> 00:09:26,890
我受邀向各部门主管介绍
I have been asked to make a presentation to the heads of department

169
00:09:26,900 --> 00:09:29,890
我们经营女装部的经验
about how we do things in Ladieswear.

170
00:09:29,900 --> 00:09:31,890
莫里先生为什么让你做这种事?
Why would Mr Moray want you to do a thing like that?

171
00:09:31,900 --> 00:09:34,890
不是莫里叫的 是威斯顿先生
It was not Moray who asked, it was Mr Weston.

172
00:09:34,900 --> 00:09:38,890
我觉得我们可以一起完成 给他们看
What I thought was, we could do it together - show them.

173
00:09:39,900 --> 00:09:41,890
我们需要投票吗? 我要投票 我要投赞成票
Do we have to vote on it? I'll vote. I'll vote yes.

174
00:09:41,900 --> 00:09:43,610
我从没出过风头
I never get to show off. 

175
00:09:43,611 --> 00:09:45,890
这可不是出风头 苏西
It's not about showing off, Susy.

176
00:09:45,900 --> 00:09:46,900
而是陈述
It's a presentment.

177
00:09:47,900 --> 00:09:49,723
克莱拉? 
Clara? 

178
00:09:49,724 --> 00:09:53,890
威斯顿先生为什么让你做这个?
Why would Mr Weston ask you to do such a thing?

179
00:09:53,900 --> 00:09:55,890
他说他想引进现代的工作方法
He said he wants to introduce modern ways of working.

180
00:09:55,900 --> 00:09:59,890
那就是了 莫里先生怎么看?
Oh, that must be it, then. What does Mr Moray think about this?

181
00:09:59,900 --> 00:10:01,900
我还没告诉他
I haven't told him yet.

182
00:10:02,900 --> 00:10:04,900
看来要招人议论了
Cat. Pigeons.

183
00:10:39,900 --> 00:10:41,890
年轻姑娘们都一样
All young girls are the same.

184
00:10:41,900 --> 00:10:43,890
十岁的时候 想变成十一岁
When we are ten, we want to be eleven,

185
00:10:43,900 --> 00:10:46,890
十一岁的时候 想变成十二岁
when we are eleven, we want to be twelve.

186
00:10:46,900 --> 00:10:49,900
我坚持认为 应该享受当下的年龄 芙罗拉
I insist you delight in the age that you are, Flora.

187
00:10:51,900 --> 00:10:54,900
我今天对德妮丝说了完全一样的话
I was saying quite the same thing to Denise today.

188
00:10:55,900 --> 00:10:58,890
德妮丝?
Denise? 

189
00:10:58,900 --> 00:11:03,890
年轻是她能胜任商场的工作的决定性优势
Her youth is her defining asset in her role in the store.

190
00:11:03,900 --> 00:11:05,900
充满热情
All that enthusiasm.

191
00:11:06,900 --> 00:11:08,890
别人几乎无法限制她
One can hardly put a cap on it.

192
00:11:08,900 --> 00:11:11,890
我已经决定了 要激发她全部的热情
I've determined to make the most of it.

193
00:11:11,900 --> 00:11:15,890
你准备怎么做呢 亲爱的?
And how will you do that, darling?

194
00:11:15,900 --> 00:11:16,900
我要让她成为榜样
I will let her serve as an example

195
00:11:16,901 --> 00:11:18,900
让别人知道该如何处理自己的工作
 to others of how to do their jobs.

196
00:11:19,900 --> 00:11:21,900
她真是个人物
She's quite something.

197
00:11:29,900 --> 00:11:32,890
你一定会迷倒并教育我们每一个人 德妮丝
I'm sure you will no doubt charm and educate every one of us, Denise.

198
00:11:32,900 --> 00:11:34,890
我只是来分享一些
All I will do is share a few things I have tried

199
00:11:34,900 --> 00:11:36,890
似乎能使我们的工作更容易的经验
which seem to make our work easier.

200
00:11:36,900 --> 00:11:39,890
我只希望资深的员工不会觉得
I only hope the more senior members of staff don't see you

201
00:11:39,900 --> 00:11:41,890
你自认为比他们高明
as placing yourself above them.

202
00:11:41,900 --> 00:11:44,890
但今天对你而言 一定特别美好 当然了
But it will be a wonderful day for you, of course.

203
00:11:44,900 --> 00:11:47,890
同事们不会讨厌德妮丝 我们非常了解她
Her colleagues won't think badly of Denise. We know her enough.

204
00:11:47,900 --> 00:11:50,890
我们都知道 她只是希望百货公司能更好
We all realise that she only wishes to be of benefit to the store.

205
00:11:50,900 --> 00:11:53,890
我相信 她会持友谊精神完成
I'm sure it will be done in the spirit of companionship.

206
00:11:53,900 --> 00:11:56,890
我也会对她介绍的方法感兴趣
I for one will be interested in what methods she has introduced.

207
00:11:56,900 --> 00:11:59,355
威斯顿先生不持任何怀疑 
Mr Weston would not countenance any doubts.

208
00:11:59,356 --> 00:12:00,890
他已经认可了吗?
You've already accepted?

209
00:12:00,900 --> 00:12:03,890
没错 我... 他问过我...
Yes. I... He asked me and...

210
00:12:03,900 --> 00:12:06,900
那你一定得充分利用这次机会了
Then you must make the most of the occasion.

211
00:12:11,900 --> 00:12:13,900
威斯顿夫人
Mrs Weston.

212
00:12:15,900 --> 00:12:19,890
我改变主意了 这是我父亲的手表
I have had a change of heart. My father's watch.

213
00:12:19,900 --> 00:12:21,355
我现在相信了 
I appreciate now that 

214
00:12:21,356 --> 00:12:24,890
你把它放在橱窗展示 是表示对我父亲的尊重
your intention is to honour my father by putting it on display.

215
00:12:24,900 --> 00:12:27,890
我没有理由拒绝你的请求
I see no good reason not to concede to your wishes.

216
00:12:27,900 --> 00:12:29,900
我非常感激
Then I am most grateful.

217
00:12:30,900 --> 00:12:32,900
山姆?
Sam?

218
00:12:33,900 --> 00:12:37,890
山姆 看来你的重头展品出现了
Sam, it seems we have your centrepiece for you.

219
00:12:37,900 --> 00:12:40,900
它有上百年的年头了 是我父亲的继承财产
It is over a hundred years old. My father inherited it.

220
00:12:43,900 --> 00:12:46,890
老实说 虽然我经常对顾客编故事
To be honest, as much as I cook up a tale for the customers,

221
00:12:46,900 --> 00:12:48,900
但我一直认为手表不过就是手表
I always thought a watch was just a watch.

222
00:12:50,900 --> 00:12:52,890
我知道我要的是神奇的东西 先生
I know I asked for something magical, sir,

223
00:12:52,900 --> 00:12:55,890
但这宝贝 我必须得让他们排队看看
but that'll have them queuing up just to take a look at it.

224
00:12:55,900 --> 00:12:57,890
我父亲用这个教我看时间
My father taught me to read the time with this.

225
00:12:57,900 --> 00:13:00,900
那是每天最精彩的时刻
It was the high point of every day.

226
00:13:01,900 --> 00:13:03,890
它让我着了魔了
It has me bewitched.

227
00:13:03,900 --> 00:13:05,890
你让我想起了自己小时候 山姆
You remind me of when I was a child, Sam.

228
00:13:05,900 --> 00:13:09,890
我也曾用过完全相同的词 它让我着了魔了
I used the self-same words about it. It had me bewitched.

229
00:13:09,900 --> 00:13:12,900
我父亲过去常常用它催眠我
My father used to hypnotise me with it.

230
00:13:13,900 --> 00:13:14,890
他在我眼前轻轻地摇晃这只手表
He would swing it gently before my eyes

231
00:13:14,900 --> 00:13:18,900
轻声说话 让我相信他把我带入了幻境
and speak softly and convince me he had induced a trance over me.

232
00:13:20,900 --> 00:13:23,890
它是个奇迹 我应该珍惜它
It is little wonder that I should treasure it so.

233
00:13:23,900 --> 00:13:25,900
我们会像你一样珍惜它的 夫人
We will treasure it just as much, ma'am.

234
00:13:29,900 --> 00:13:34,890
有件事 我希望你能考虑考虑 莫里
There is one aspect of this matter for which I would ask your consideration, Moray.

235
00:13:35,900 --> 00:13:40,890
我父亲希望把那只手表传给我的丈夫
My father's wishes - that the watch be passed on to the man I marry.

236
00:13:40,900 --> 00:13:42,475
汤姆不知道 
Tom does not know. 

237
00:13:42,476 --> 00:13:45,890
如果你能保密 我将感激不尽
I would appreciate it if you made no mention.

238
00:13:45,900 --> 00:13:48,890
是 是 当然了 还轮不到我来告诉他
Why, yes, yes, of course. It's not my place to tell him.

239
00:13:48,900 --> 00:13:52,890
我意识到您对它的依恋 威斯顿夫人
I realise how deeply attached you are to it, Mrs Weston.

240
00:13:52,900 --> 00:13:54,900
请叫我凯瑟琳
Please, call me Katherine.

241
00:14:00,900 --> 00:14:04,890
我从没见过这么惊人的东西
I never laid my eyes on anything quite so marvellous.

242
00:14:04,900 --> 00:14:06,890
你觉得它值多少钱 达德利先生?
How much do you suppose it's worth, Mr Dudley?

243
00:14:06,900 --> 00:14:09,890
值我们俩下半辈子的工资 山姆
It would keep the two of us in wages for the rest of our lives, Sam.

244
00:14:09,900 --> 00:14:13,890
但是 你能感觉到
Aye, but you get the feeling that this is worth more

245
00:14:13,900 --> 00:14:16,900
它比钱更值钱
than pounds, shillings and pence.

246
00:14:37,900 --> 00:14:40,900
我希望你没有再次干预莫里的事 乔纳斯
I hope you are not meddling in Moray's affairs again, Jonas.

247
00:14:41,900 --> 00:14:43,895
就如你所见 达德利先生
As you can see, Mr Dudley, 

248
00:14:43,896 --> 00:14:45,890
我只是在处理自己的事
I'm simply going about my duties.

249
00:14:45,900 --> 00:14:48,900
就是我看不到的才让我担心
It is what I cannot see that concerns me.

250
00:14:49,900 --> 00:14:51,890
我看见莫里和威斯顿夫人在一起
I have watched Moray with Mrs Weston.

251
00:14:51,900 --> 00:14:54,980
他为什么对她这么热忱 这么亲密?
Why is he so cordial, so intimate with her? 

252
00:14:54,981 --> 00:14:56,890
发生什么事了?
What is going on?

253
00:14:56,902 --> 00:14:58,890
先生 我不能代表莫里先生
I cannot speak on Mr Moray's behalf, sir.

254
00:14:58,900 --> 00:15:02,890
你说得越礼貌 就越是在狡猾地逃避我的问题
The more polite your tongue, the more slippery you are at avoiding my questions.

255
00:15:02,900 --> 00:15:04,890
我无意冒犯
I mean no offence.

256
00:15:04,900 --> 00:15:09,890
你也无意开诚布公 跟我说实话
Yet you have no wish to be open and honest with me, either.

257
00:15:09,900 --> 00:15:11,890
我知道是你在操纵他
I know that it is you leading him down this path

258
00:15:11,900 --> 00:15:15,100
因为你们俩一个字也不说 
and since I can prise no information from either of you, 

259
00:15:15,101 --> 00:15:19,900
我得说 你以为你最清楚吗?
 I will say this. Do you suppose you know best?

260
00:15:21,900 --> 00:15:24,890
我希望你考虑一下现状 先生
I ask you to consider the circumstances, sir.

261
00:15:24,900 --> 00:15:29,890
谁拥有天堂百货 你看到了正义存在吗?
Who owns The Paradise? Is there justice in what you see?

262
00:15:30,900 --> 00:15:33,066
如果汤姆・威斯顿掌握权力 
Do you believe life will get easier

263
00:15:33,067 --> 00:15:35,900
你觉得我们任何人的生活能更好过吗?
 for any of us while Tom Weston holds the whip?

264
00:15:36,900 --> 00:15:38,900
尤其是莫里先生
Especially for Mr Moray.

265
00:15:40,900 --> 00:15:42,757
你能感觉到自己在看它吗? 
Can you feel your eyes drawn to it?

266
00:15:42,758 --> 00:15:44,900
好似你的视线无法从它身上移开?
 Like you can't stop looking at it?

267
00:15:46,900 --> 00:15:48,890
当然 这还不是它的美妙之处
That's not the beauty of it, of course.

268
00:15:48,900 --> 00:15:51,890
虽然它的确是个漂亮的家伙!
Well, it is a handsome thing!

269
00:15:51,900 --> 00:15:55,890
但这里面的东西 是无法解释的力量
But what we have here is a power beyond explanation.

270
00:15:55,900 --> 00:15:58,890
让我宁愿为它万死不辞
May I fall down and die.

271
00:15:58,900 --> 00:16:00,900
难道没觉得仿佛时间都静止了吗?
Does it not feel as though time itself has stopped?

272
00:16:03,900 --> 00:16:05,890
你有手表吗 先生?
Do you own a watch, sir?

273
00:16:05,900 --> 00:16:07,890
你看起来很了解时间的重要性
You look like a man who knows the importance of time,

274
00:16:07,900 --> 00:16:09,890
谁不希望自己的口袋里有一块古老的锡铁表呢
who wouldn't have any old piece of tin in your pocket.

275
00:16:09,900 --> 00:16:11,900
我是说对了 还是说对了?
Am I right or am I right?

276
00:16:13,900 --> 00:16:17,900
这个手表 不在于是否有人买得起它
This watch here, it's not a matter of whether a fella can afford it.

277
00:16:19,900 --> 00:16:21,900
而在于是否有人买得起 而不想拥有它
It's whether a fella can afford not to own it.

278
00:16:24,900 --> 00:16:28,890
如果我们需要决定一件事情 我们就投票
If there's an issue we need to decide upon, we vote on it.

279
00:16:28,900 --> 00:16:31,420
我本来不想分红 
I didn't want to share my bonus 

280
00:16:31,423 --> 00:16:32,890
但要投票决定时 我就同意了
but when it was voted in, then I did.

281
00:16:32,900 --> 00:16:35,155
我觉得我现在工作更努力了 
I think I work harder now 

282
00:16:35,156 --> 00:16:36,890
因为如果姑娘们在为我工作
because if the girls are earning commission for me,

283
00:16:36,900 --> 00:16:38,890
我也应该为她们工作
I ought to make commission for them, too.

284
00:16:38,900 --> 00:16:42,890
我们甚至投票决定今天是否来这里做这个介绍
We even had a vote about whether we would talk to you all today.

285
00:16:42,900 --> 00:16:45,890
作为销售员 我感觉自己是团队一员时
As a shop girl, I did my best work when I felt involved,

286
00:16:45,900 --> 00:16:47,890
工作效率最高
part of a team.

287
00:16:48,900 --> 00:16:50,890
我觉得 如果我们都很享受
I think if we all enjoy ourselves,

288
00:16:50,900 --> 00:16:53,890
顾客也会愿意来这里
then customers will enjoy coming here.

289
00:16:53,900 --> 00:16:57,890
以上就是全部 谢谢大家
I think that's everything. Thank you for coming today.

290
00:16:57,900 --> 00:17:00,890
也许我们应该投票决定是否应该结束
Perhaps we should have a vote to see if our little presentation's over.

291
00:17:05,900 --> 00:17:07,261
非常好! 
Splendid! 

292
00:17:07,262 --> 00:17:11,890
今天 德妮丝小姐和她的姑娘们的展示
What Miss Denise and her girls have illustrated for us today

293
00:17:11,900 --> 00:17:14,890
说明我们绝不能固步自封
is that we must not rest on our laurels.

294
00:17:14,900 --> 00:17:18,890
过去的成功秘诀不一定适用于今天
What has brought success in the past will not do today.

295
00:17:18,900 --> 00:17:21,181
很清楚 我们最好意识到
Clearly, we would do well to see 

296
00:17:21,182 --> 00:17:24,890
今天介绍的方法是前进的方向
that today's presentation leads the way.

297
00:17:24,900 --> 00:17:26,958
她不令人敬畏吗 莫里? 
Is she not formidable, Moray? 

298
00:17:26,959 --> 00:17:29,900
她们都令人敬畏 先生 她们都令人敬畏
They all were, sir. They all were.

299
00:17:44,900 --> 00:17:46,890
大家都对我非常好
Everybody was so kind to me.

300
00:17:46,900 --> 00:17:50,900
他们都来问我问题 来祝贺我
They were full of questions and congratulations.

301
00:17:52,900 --> 00:17:55,900
你觉得如何 亲爱的?
What did you think, sweetheart?

302
00:17:56,900 --> 00:17:59,890
告诉我 老实说
Tell me. Tell me honestly.

303
00:17:59,900 --> 00:18:01,900
我只在乎你的看法
Your opinion's the only one that matters.

304
00:18:02,900 --> 00:18:05,900
我...
I...

305
00:18:06,900 --> 00:18:10,890
我很高兴你为这里带来了活力 德妮丝
I delight in seeing you light up this place, Denise,

306
00:18:10,900 --> 00:18:15,890
但是我们不能忘记 事情不该是这样
but we must not forget, it is not meant to be this way.

307
00:18:15,900 --> 00:18:18,900
我们不应该在他们的怜悯或者帮助下生活
We are not meant to be under their mercy or favour.

308
00:18:19,900 --> 00:18:22,900
这里应该属于我们 你知道吗?
This place should be ours. Do you see?

309
00:18:24,900 --> 00:18:26,890
当然了
Of course.

310
00:18:26,900 --> 00:18:28,890
有时候我会激动得忘乎所以
Sometimes I get carried away.

311
00:18:28,900 --> 00:18:29,890
我必须尽全力
I must do my best.

312
00:18:29,900 --> 00:18:32,295
这就是我们必须竭尽全力 
That is why we must go to any lengths 

313
00:18:32,296 --> 00:18:34,890
让我重新拥有天堂百货的原因
to make The Paradise mine again.

314
00:18:34,900 --> 00:18:36,900
而你就是我的女主角
And then you will be my leading lady.

315
00:18:46,900 --> 00:18:48,890
我今天简直就是台推销机器 艾德蒙
I was a selling machine today, Edmund.

316
00:18:48,900 --> 00:18:49,890
我真希望你能看到我们今天的表现
I wish you could have seen us.

317
00:18:49,900 --> 00:18:52,890
你一直都表现得像是一台推销机器 山姆
You're always a selling machine, Sam.

318
00:18:52,900 --> 00:18:54,890
所有人都有一技之长
Every man has to be good at one thing.

319
00:18:54,900 --> 00:18:56,890
我拼命兜售 就好像今天是世界末日一样!
I was peddling like it was the end of the world!

320
00:18:56,900 --> 00:19:00,900
你想知道为什么吗?
And you want to know why?

321
00:19:01,900 --> 00:19:02,890
我的幸运物
My lucky charm.

322
00:19:02,900 --> 00:19:06,890
它怎么在你的口袋里? 这东西可值一大笔钱
What are you doing with that in your pocket? It's worth a fortune.

323
00:19:06,900 --> 00:19:08,096
我就想揣上几个小时 
I thought, for a few hours, 

324
00:19:08,097 --> 00:19:09,890
商店已经关门了 没有人会注意到
while the shop's closed, no-one will notice.

325
00:19:09,900 --> 00:19:12,890
想感受一下怀揣宝物的感觉
See what it feels like to have something precious in my pocket.

326
00:19:12,900 --> 00:19:15,890
实话告诉你 感觉棒极了
And to be honest, it feels marvellous.

327
00:19:15,900 --> 00:19:18,890
这可不像你 山姆 招惹是非
It's not like you, Sam, to flirt with trouble.

328
00:19:18,900 --> 00:19:20,890
我知道 我在陈列室的原位上铺了一块黑布
I know. I put a black cloth over the spot in the cabinet.

329
00:19:20,900 --> 00:19:22,890
没人会注意到它不见了的
No-one will even notice it's missing.

330
00:19:22,900 --> 00:19:24,890
但如果你不小心摔了它或者弄丢了怎么办?
But what if you drop it or you lose it?

331
00:19:24,900 --> 00:19:27,890
我看到它躺在那里 光彩夺目
I saw it there, spellbinding,

332
00:19:27,900 --> 00:19:29,890
我难以自持
I couldn't resist it.

333
00:19:29,900 --> 00:19:32,900
它的质感 它的设计理念
The feel of it. The idea of it.

334
00:19:33,900 --> 00:19:35,181
你得承认 艾德蒙 
You have to admit, Edmund, 

335
00:19:35,182 --> 00:19:36,890
这是个尤物 有生命的瑰宝
it's a thing of beauty, a living wonder.

336
00:19:36,900 --> 00:19:38,890
这确实很美
It's certainly splendid

337
00:19:38,900 --> 00:19:41,890
即时这样我也不认为你应该把它拿出来
but I wouldn't thank you for having that in my pocket.

338
00:19:41,900 --> 00:19:43,039
只是这样握着它 
Just by having it here, 

339
00:19:43,040 --> 00:19:44,890
我就觉得我似乎又高大了一点
I feel an inch taller,

340
00:19:44,900 --> 00:19:47,890
更英俊潇洒 更无所畏惧了
more handsome, more fearless.

341
00:19:47,900 --> 00:19:49,890
世界之王
King of the world.

342
00:19:49,900 --> 00:19:53,154
这种感觉有一个名字 那就是诱惑
There's a name for that. It's called temptation. 

343
00:19:53,155 --> 00:19:54,890
你应该抵制诱惑
The thing is to resist it.

344
00:19:54,900 --> 00:19:58,900
啊 你已经老了 就是这样 畏手畏脚的了!
Ah, you're old, that's all. Lost your daring, man!

345
00:20:00,900 --> 00:20:03,890
快点 问我几点了
Ask me what time it is.

346
00:20:03,900 --> 00:20:07,900
- 几点了? - 山姆的时间 没错
- What time is it? - Sam's time, that's what.

347
00:20:08,900 --> 00:20:10,900
是山姆扬眉吐气的时间
Sam's time to be on top.

348
00:20:14,900 --> 00:20:17,890
他在耍我
He is toying with me.

349
00:20:17,900 --> 00:20:19,792
他知道如果他把那些赞美和成就
He knows that if he can heap praise and advancement 

350
00:20:19,793 --> 00:20:21,341
加于德妮丝身上
onto Denise that

351
00:20:21,342 --> 00:20:22,890
我会感到煎熬
 it will torment me.

352
00:20:22,900 --> 00:20:24,890
那么您要做出选择 先生
Then you have a choice, sir.

353
00:20:24,900 --> 00:20:26,715
要么让他占上风
You can let him win the day,

354
00:20:26,716 --> 00:20:29,540
要么你可以表现出同样的老道和勇敢 
or you can meet him with as much 

355
00:20:29,541 --> 00:20:30,890
与他正面交锋
cunning and daring.

356
00:20:30,900 --> 00:20:34,196
如果您能成功地让威斯顿先生清楚地意识到
If you manage to plant into Mr Weston's mind 

357
00:20:34,197 --> 00:20:36,855
他的妻子在对您献殷勤的话 
the clear idea that his wife is pursuing you,

358
00:20:36,856 --> 00:20:38,900
他会想找个人聊一聊的
 he will want someone to talk to.

359
00:20:41,900 --> 00:20:44,900
我已经和他建立起了些许的信任
I have already established some trust between he and I.

360
00:20:46,900 --> 00:20:51,890
要是我让他发现我对您抱有怨言的话
If I let him see that I hold a festering resentment towards you,

361
00:20:52,900 --> 00:20:53,900
他会对我更加信赖
he might begin to confide in me.

362
00:21:25,400 --> 00:21:26,890
怎么了 乔纳斯?
What is it, Jonas?

363
00:21:26,900 --> 00:21:29,900
哦 请原谅我 先生
Oh, forgive me, sir.

364
00:21:30,900 --> 00:21:33,890
我不应该表现出这样沮丧的状态
I should not let my frustration show in such a manner.

365
00:21:33,900 --> 00:21:36,890
恕我冒昧 让我回去工作吧
If I may, I will return to my duties.

366
00:21:36,900 --> 00:21:39,890
你因为什么事情不开心吗?
Something has upset you?

367
00:21:39,900 --> 00:21:41,890
感谢您的关心 先生
I appreciate your concern, sir,

368
00:21:41,900 --> 00:21:44,890
但是我不能用我的对上司不满的情绪来麻烦您
but I cannot trouble you with my grievances against my employer.

369
00:21:44,900 --> 00:21:47,890
我这样的行为真是太可悲了 恕我冒昧...
It was petty of me to behave in this way. If I may...

370
00:21:47,900 --> 00:21:51,900
莫里? 他做了什么让你这样不安?
Moray? What has he done to disturb you?

371
00:21:53,900 --> 00:21:56,890
这些年来 我尽职尽责的服侍这个男人
I have served that man for some years with loyalty and dedication

372
00:21:56,900 --> 00:21:58,890
十分恪尽职守
beyond the call of duty.

373
00:21:58,900 --> 00:22:02,900
难道我不值得得到雇主的信任吗?
Do I not deserve the reward of my employer's trust?

374
00:22:03,900 --> 00:22:08,890
不知为什么我觉得信任感对我非常重要 先生
I don't know why it matters so much to me to be trusted, sir,

375
00:22:08,900 --> 00:22:10,890
但是确实非常重要
but it does.

376
00:22:10,900 --> 00:22:14,900
在我看来 你想错了方向 乔纳斯
It seems to me you have the equation the wrong way around, Jonas.

377
00:22:16,900 --> 00:22:20,900
你应该扪心自问 莫里是否真的值得你的忠诚
You should ask yourself if Moray is worthy of your loyalty.

378
00:22:23,900 --> 00:22:26,052
她亲自告诉我的... 凯瑟琳・威斯顿 
She told me herself... Katherine Weston. 

379
00:22:26,053 --> 00:22:26,890
那块表具有魔力
That watch has powers.

380
00:22:26,900 --> 00:22:28,890
催眠的魔力
Hypnotic powers.

381
00:22:28,900 --> 00:22:30,890
她的家族里 过去的时候
Her family, in her family, going back,

382
00:22:30,900 --> 00:22:32,890
他们会用表来催眠对方
they used to mesmerise each other with it.

383
00:22:32,900 --> 00:22:34,890
她的父亲精通于此
Her father was the master of it.

384
00:22:34,900 --> 00:22:36,890
要不然你想他是如何得到财富的
How else do you suppose he got his riches?

385
00:22:36,900 --> 00:22:39,890
魔力 不可思议的魔力
Powers. Incredible powers.

386
00:22:39,900 --> 00:22:42,052
把你那套说辞留给顾客们吧 山姆 
Save your patter for the customers, Sam. 

387
00:22:42,053 --> 00:22:42,890
我站在这儿
As I stand here.

388
00:22:42,900 --> 00:22:44,890
好吧 坐在这儿 我自己可以感觉到
Well, sit here. I felt it myself.

389
00:22:44,900 --> 00:22:47,890
我相信他 什么是催眠的 山姆?
I believe him. What is hypnotic, Sam?

390
00:22:47,900 --> 00:22:51,890
是催眠 苏西 就是一种睡眠
Hypnosis, Susy, well, it's a kind of sleep.

391
00:22:51,900 --> 00:22:54,890
好吧 也不完全是睡觉 就好像...
Well, not sleep exactly. It's like...

392
00:22:54,900 --> 00:22:56,655
啊 和入睡的状态不同 
Ah, it's not like being asleep. 

393
00:22:56,656 --> 00:22:58,890
就好像你在这儿但其实不在这儿
It's like being here but not being here.

394
00:22:58,900 --> 00:23:00,890
苏西即使是在最佳状态的时候也是这种感觉
That's what Susy feels like at the best of times.

395
00:23:00,900 --> 00:23:02,890
就好像是眩晕 那种感觉
It's like being dazzled, kind of thing.

396
00:23:02,900 --> 00:23:04,295
什么 像喝醉了一样吗? 
What, like being drunk? 

397
00:23:04,296 --> 00:23:05,890
你怎么知道喝醉了是什么感觉?
What do you know about being drunk?

398
00:23:05,900 --> 00:23:08,900
不是 催眠 就是...
No. Hypnosis, it's...

399
00:23:09,900 --> 00:23:13,890
被催眠了就好像是处在一个无所不能的世界里
Being hypnotised is like being in a world where everything is possible.

400
00:23:13,900 --> 00:23:16,890
如果你想跳舞 就可以像芭蕾舞者翩然起舞
If you want to dance you'll be like a ballerina.

401
00:23:16,900 --> 00:23:19,890
要是你想唱歌 你的歌喉会像鸣鸟一样悦耳
If you want to sing, you'll warble like a songbird.

402
00:23:19,900 --> 00:23:20,890
你好像是活在你的愿望里
It's like being in a kind of wish.

403
00:23:20,900 --> 00:23:22,890
那我们所有人都应该一直被催眠啊
We should all do it all the time.

404
00:23:22,900 --> 00:23:24,768
哦 我想被催眠的
Oh, I want to be hypnotic.

405
00:23:24,769 --> 00:23:25,890
是被催眠
 Hypnotised.

406
00:23:25,900 --> 00:23:27,890
你会催眠吗? 能不能把我催眠 山姆?
Can you? Can you hypnotise me, Sam?

407
00:23:27,900 --> 00:23:29,890
小心点 苏西 他会把你弄昏之后
Careful, Susy, he'll put you under

408
00:23:29,900 --> 00:23:31,890
告诉你把你每周的薪水交给他
then tell you to give him your wages every week.

409
00:23:31,900 --> 00:23:33,890
要是你想体验一把灵魂出窍的感觉
If you are looking for an out of body experience,

410
00:23:33,900 --> 00:23:35,890
那你可找对人啦 苏西
you have come to the right fella, Susy.

411
00:23:35,900 --> 00:23:37,890
今夜 商店打烊后
Tonight. After we close.

412
00:23:37,900 --> 00:23:40,890
- 我们都能来吗? - 为什么不呢?
- Can we all come? - Why not?

413
00:23:40,900 --> 00:23:43,900
来吧 在大堂 我们打烊之后
Go on, then. In the Great Hall. After we close.

414
00:23:46,900 --> 00:23:49,257
我想说做的好 梅尔托 
I wanted to say well done, Myrtle. 

415
00:23:49,258 --> 00:23:50,890
对我说 先生?
To me, sir?

416
00:23:50,900 --> 00:23:53,101
那些你为了新的美食厅制作的面包 
The breads, pies, pastries you've cooked for 

417
00:23:53,102 --> 00:23:54,890
馅饼 糕点 让人口水直流啊
the new Food Hall are mouth-watering.

418
00:23:54,900 --> 00:23:58,890
- 销售额非常不错 - 真的吗 先生?
- The sales are extraordinary. - Are they, sir?

419
00:23:58,900 --> 00:24:00,890
- 我是说 谢谢您 先生 - 是的
I mean, thank you, sir. Oh, yes.

420
00:24:00,900 --> 00:24:03,890
现在我们必须更进一步
Now we must step up the splendour.

421
00:24:03,900 --> 00:24:07,890
你的厨房做出点特别的东西
Perhaps something special from your kitchen

422
00:24:07,900 --> 00:24:09,890
让美食厅成为天堂百货的谈资
to make the Food Hall the talk of The Paradise.

423
00:24:09,900 --> 00:24:11,890
听上去真不错啊 先生
That sounds marvellous, sir.

424
00:24:11,900 --> 00:24:13,900
那么你会给我来点什么?
So what will you provide me with?

425
00:24:15,900 --> 00:24:18,890
您心中想的是什么? 威斯顿先生
What did you have in mind, Mr Weston?

426
00:24:18,900 --> 00:24:23,890
我想的是你会给我来点让人难以抗拒的东西
I had in mind that you would offer me something truly irresistible.

427
00:24:23,900 --> 00:24:27,900
那种能放在橱窗展示的东西 梅尔托
Something to put in the front window, Myrtle.

428
00:24:28,900 --> 00:24:31,900
它的美甚至让珠宝相形见绌
Something that might outshine even a jewel.

429
00:24:35,900 --> 00:24:37,890
我尽力 先生
I will, sir.

430
00:24:37,900 --> 00:24:40,890
让我好好地想一想 看看我能想出点什么来
Let me just scratch my head for a while, see what I can come up with.

431
00:24:40,900 --> 00:24:42,900
当然了 我会很快再和你聊的
Of course. We'll speak again soon.

432
00:25:04,900 --> 00:25:06,890
- 凯瑟琳 - 哦!
- Katherine. - Oh!

433
00:25:06,900 --> 00:25:08,900
