Your father's watch has proven to be quite a success.

434
00:25:10,900 --> 00:25:12,890
你说的对 当然了
You were right, of course.

435
00:25:12,900 --> 00:25:13,890
我就知道你是对的
I should have known you would be.

436
00:25:13,900 --> 00:25:15,890
它是一件那么华丽的珍宝
Well, it's such a magnificent treasure,

437
00:25:15,900 --> 00:25:18,890
我现在知道了你独自珍藏的原因了
I can understand why you might want to keep it to yourself.

438
00:25:18,900 --> 00:25:21,900
哦 但是我并不想永远留在手里
Oh, but I did not always wish to keep it.

439
00:25:23,900 --> 00:25:26,900
有些话我难以启齿 你听了也会觉得不可思议
I know it is difficult to say, and to hear, such a thing.

440
00:25:28,900 --> 00:25:31,900
但是似乎于我而言 最好还是将事实告诉你
But it seems to me now it is better to tell the truth.

441
00:25:33,900 --> 00:25:36,890
我们一起经历的了这么多的事情 你和我
We have been through so much together, you and I.

442
00:25:36,900 --> 00:25:39,900
我们之间当然不需要任何的隐藏了
Surely we have no room for pretences any more.

443
00:25:42,900 --> 00:25:45,890
我必须要坦白
I have a confession to make.

444
00:25:45,900 --> 00:25:48,900
我没有把这块怀表给汤姆的原因
Why I have never passed the watch on to Tom.

445
00:25:49,900 --> 00:25:52,900
因为我的父亲想要把它给你
My father wanted you to have it.

446
00:25:53,900 --> 00:25:55,890
真的吗 凯瑟琳?
Is that true, Katherine?

447
00:25:55,900 --> 00:26:00,890
你父亲从来没有对我表现出如此的喜爱
Your father did not exhibit such a fondness for me.

448
00:26:00,900 --> 00:26:02,890
是真的
It is true.

449
00:26:02,900 --> 00:26:04,900
差不多吧
Almost true.

450
00:26:06,900 --> 00:26:08,900
我想让他把表给你 在我们的...
I wanted him to give it to you at our...

451
00:26:10,900 --> 00:26:13,900
我似乎无法让这种念头消散
I can't seem to let that idea go.

452
00:26:15,900 --> 00:26:17,900
也许这就是我无法把表给汤姆的原因吧
Perhaps that is why I can't face giving it to Tom.

453
00:26:22,900 --> 00:26:26,890
过往发生的一切事情 我知道你无法原谅我 
I know you can never forgive me for what happened,

454
00:26:26,900 --> 00:26:29,890
因为我那样对你 对你的...
for what I did to you, and to your...

455
00:26:29,900 --> 00:26:31,900
请别糟蹋了我的好意
Don't spoil it, please.

456
00:26:32,900 --> 00:26:34,900
这么想对汤姆不公平
It feels unfair to Tom to feel this way.

457
00:26:36,900 --> 00:26:38,890
这就是为什么我这样下定决心
Which is why I have decided it is best

458
00:26:38,900 --> 00:26:40,073
汤姆永远也不会知道
he never knows that 

459
00:26:40,074 --> 00:26:41,900
这块表本是应该传给我的丈夫的
my father intended his watch to go to my husband.

460
00:26:42,900 --> 00:26:45,900
我明白
I understand.

461
00:26:48,900 --> 00:26:50,900
你注意到了吗?
Have you noticed?

462
00:26:53,900 --> 00:26:56,900
我们又像以前一样沿街漫步了
We have fallen into promenading along the street, as we used to.

463
00:26:59,900 --> 00:27:01,900
有些东西永远不会消失
Some things are never lost.

464
00:27:43,900 --> 00:27:45,900
- 威斯顿夫人 - 请坐过来 克莱拉 
- Mrs Weston. - Sit with me, Clara.

465
00:27:53,900 --> 00:27:55,890
我正想和你私下里聊一聊
I was hoping to speak with you privately.

466
00:27:55,900 --> 00:27:58,890
你为什么想要和我聊天呢 夫人?
Why would you wish to speak to me, ma'am?

467
00:27:58,900 --> 00:28:01,890
你大概是德妮丝最亲近的朋友了吧
You are perhaps closest to Denise.

468
00:28:01,900 --> 00:28:04,890
我在担忧她会怎么想那块表的事情
I have been concerned how she might be feeling about the watch.

469
00:28:04,900 --> 00:28:05,850
那块表? 
The watch? 

470
00:28:05,851 --> 00:28:08,890
她对那块表很在意吗? 威斯顿夫人
I don't know that she's greatly aware of it, Mrs Weston.

471
00:28:08,900 --> 00:28:10,097
我想说的是 
What I mean is, 

472
00:28:10,098 --> 00:28:13,890
