that I should entrust Moray with such a precious thing from my family.

473
00:28:13,900 --> 00:28:17,890
我的理解是 那块表是为了促销 夫人
My understanding is that it was here for a promotion, ma'am.

474
00:28:17,900 --> 00:28:19,890
是的 是的 是这样
Yes. Yes, that is so.

475
00:28:19,900 --> 00:28:24,890
但是这种事很容易被误解
But these things can easily be misinterpreted,

476
00:28:24,900 --> 00:28:26,890
考虑到是莫里这样的人
given the kind of man Moray is,

477
00:28:26,900 --> 00:28:29,900
你我心里都清楚
as both you and I know.

478
00:28:31,900 --> 00:28:33,890
那他是怎样的人?
And what kind of man is that?

479
00:28:33,900 --> 00:28:35,900
一个受情绪所控的人
A man ruled by his passions.

480
00:28:37,900 --> 00:28:39,890
我不想让任何人觉得我给了他鼓励
I would not like anyone to think I had encouraged him.

481
00:28:39,900 --> 00:28:41,900
任何人 你的意思是说德妮丝?
By anyone, you mean Denise?

482
00:28:44,900 --> 00:28:46,900
你为什么不考虑一下德妮丝的感受?
Why would you be concerned for Denise's feelings?

483
00:28:49,900 --> 00:28:53,890
现在 我们对另一个女人的同情
There comes a point when our fellow-feeling for another woman

484
00:28:53,900 --> 00:28:54,900
最能触动我们的心
is what touches us most.

485
00:28:57,900 --> 00:29:02,890
坦率的讲 自从莫里伤害了我们 克莱拉
Frankly, since Moray has hurt both you and me, Clara,

486
00:29:02,900 --> 00:29:05,566
我们的同情心已经没有了 不是吗 
our sympathies go, do they not, 

487
00:29:05,567 --> 00:29:07,900
对那些现在还爱着他
to the woman who loves him now...

488
00:29:10,900 --> 00:29:12,900
...还信任他的女人的同情心?
..who trusts him now?

489
00:29:13,900 --> 00:29:15,890
夫人 你是在告诉我他...
Ma'am, are you telling me that he has...

490
00:29:15,900 --> 00:29:18,900
你和我一样了解他 克莱拉
You know the kind of man he is as well as I do, Clara.

491
00:29:23,900 --> 00:29:25,900
现在 我要你放松 苏西
Now, I want you to relax, Susy.

492
00:29:27,900 --> 00:29:29,890
放松
Relax.

493
00:29:29,900 --> 00:29:31,900
放松
Relax.

494
00:29:32,900 --> 00:29:37,900
- 放松 - 或许你只要放慢呼吸
- Relax. - Perhaps if you just breathe gently.

495
00:29:40,900 --> 00:29:41,900
现在...
Now...

496
00:29:43,900 --> 00:29:46,890
我要你看着这块表
I want you to look at the watch.

497
00:29:46,900 --> 00:29:48,900
我要你相信这块表的力量
I want you to believe in the power that is in this watch.

498
00:29:51,900 --> 00:29:53,890
它是你眼中唯一能看到的
It is the only thing that your eyes can see,

499
00:29:53,900 --> 00:29:55,900
它是世上仅有的东西
the only thing in the world.

500
00:29:56,900 --> 00:29:59,900
让你的眼睛跟随着它
Let your eyes follow the watch.

501
00:30:01,900 --> 00:30:05,900
你能感觉到你的眼睛变得很重 很累
You can feel your eyes growing heavy, tired.

502
00:30:07,900 --> 00:30:09,890
你感觉到你想要闭上双眼
You can feel you want to close your eyes.

503
00:30:09,900 --> 00:30:13,900
让你的眼皮放下来 闭上
Let your eyelids fall, closed.

504
00:30:14,900 --> 00:30:16,900
闭上眼睛
Closed.

505
00:30:19,900 --> 00:30:22,989
你依然能看到这块表 苏西 
You can still see the watch, Susy, 

506
00:30:22,990 --> 00:30:24,890
因为它在你脑海里
because the watch is in your mind.

507
00:30:24,900 --> 00:30:28,900
这感觉很奇妙 是你从未体会过的美妙
It feels wonderful. It is the best you have ever felt.

508
00:30:30,900 --> 00:30:33,900
现在我要你伸出你的双手 苏西
Now I want you to hold out your hands for me, Susy.

509
00:30:39,900 --> 00:30:42,900
我要在你的两手间放一只铅笔
I'm going to put a pencil in between your fingers.

510
00:30:45,900 --> 00:30:46,900
你能感觉到吗?
Can you feel that?

511
00:30:47,900 --> 00:30:50,890
现在这只铅笔夹在你的指尖上
Now the pencil is becoming stuck to your fingertips.

512
00:30:50,900 --> 00:30:53,890
这只表想要你感受铅笔在你的指尖有多么牢固
The watch wants you to feel how stuck the pencil is.

513
00:30:53,900 --> 00:30:55,890
你想让它掉下去但是你做不到
You want to let go of it but you can't

514
00:30:55,900 --> 00:30:58,900
因为它已经粘在你的指尖上 它不会掉的
because it's stuck to your fingertips. It won't drop.

515
00:31:02,900 --> 00:31:05,890
现在我要从你的指尖上拿走铅笔 苏西
Now I'm going to take the pencil from your fingertips, Susy,

516
00:31:05,900 --> 00:31:08,900
因为这只表想要你放开铅笔
because the watch wants you to let it go...

517
00:31:09,900 --> 00:31:11,900
现在!
now!

518
00:31:13,900 --> 00:31:18,890
当我一吹口哨 苏西 你就睁开眼睛 慢慢地
When I whistle a tune, Susy, you will open your eyes, slowly 

519
00:31:18,900 --> 00:31:22,890
慢慢地 当你睁开眼睛 
slowly, and when you open your eyes

520
00:31:22,900 --> 00:31:24,900
你的脑海中只有一件事
you will have only one thought in your mind.

521
00:31:25,900 --> 00:31:28,900
我一定要请山姆喝杯啤酒
I must buy Sam a beer.

522
00:31:30,900 --> 00:31:33,890
我要请山姆喝杯啤酒
I will buy Sam a beer.

523
00:31:33,900 --> 00:31:36,890
山姆是个好小伙 山姆是个英俊的野兽
Sam is a fine lad. Sam is a handsome beast.

524
00:31:36,900 --> 00:31:40,900
一个女孩会为山姆这样的小伙倾心
A girl could fall for a lad like Sam.

525
00:31:41,900 --> 00:31:43,900
请山姆喝一杯
Buy Sam a beer.

526
00:31:53,900 --> 00:31:56,890
我们今晚要去三冠酒店吗?
Are we going over to the Three Crowns tonight?

527
00:31:56,900 --> 00:31:58,900
我要请山姆喝一杯
I want to buy Sam a beer.

528
00:32:06,900 --> 00:32:10,890
乔纳斯 非常感谢你今晚能来
Jonas, thank you for coming out here at night.

529
00:32:10,900 --> 00:32:11,900
我们喝一杯怎么样?
Shall we have a drink?

530
00:32:18,900 --> 00:32:22,471
我以前从未发现山姆是这么英俊 
I never realised how handsome Sam is before. 

531
00:32:22,472 --> 00:32:23,900
我真为他着迷
I've quite fallen for him.

532
00:32:27,900 --> 00:32:30,890
我能看出来 乔纳斯 你是一个
I see in you, Jonas, a man

533
00:32:30,900 --> 00:32:34,890
只想为你的雇主专心服务的人
who wishes only to be of service to his employer.

534
00:32:34,900 --> 00:32:36,890
遗憾的是 我们已经有了共识
Sadly, we have established, have we not,

535
00:32:36,900 --> 00:32:39,900
莫里不值得你对他这么忠诚 不是吗?
that Moray is undeserving of your loyalty?

536
00:32:41,900 --> 00:32:43,900
我知道你的感受
I know how you feel.

537
00:32:45,900 --> 00:32:50,890
我和我的妻子诚心诚意地让莫里回到这
My wife and I have in good faith brought Moray back here,

538
00:32:50,900 --> 00:32:55,890
给他一个值得信任并负责任的职位
given him a position of responsibility and trust,

539
00:32:56,900 --> 00:32:59,467
但我仍感觉他在密谋
yet I have the feeling he's plotting 

540
00:32:59,468 --> 00:33:02,890
想从我们身边夺走天堂百货
to take The Paradise away from us.

541
00:33:02,900 --> 00:33:06,890
如果他真是这样 先生 他隐藏的可够好的
Well, if he is, sir, he's keeping it well hidden.

542
00:33:06,900 --> 00:33:08,900
关键是 乔纳斯 
The point is, Jonas, 

543
00:33:08,901 --> 00:33:12,900
我看重并且信任你对商场所付出一切
I value and trust your dedication to the store.

544
00:33:14,900 --> 00:33:17,890
我必须要承认 先生 天堂百货所缺少的
I do have to admit, sir, that what The Paradise sorely needs is

545
00:33:17,900 --> 00:33:19,890
正是像您这样的人
a man, like you,

546
00:33:19,900 --> 00:33:24,890
让这个地方的荣誉能得以恢复
to restore some honour to the place.

547
00:33:24,900 --> 00:33:28,900
一个与众不同的战士 我们怎能不跟随您呢?
A soldier of distinction - how can we not follow you?

548
00:33:31,900 --> 00:33:33,890
想想看我能在一个您这样
To think that I am working for a man

549
00:33:33,900 --> 00:33:36,900
勇于为国家奉献的人手下工作
who served his country so heroically.

550
00:33:39,900 --> 00:33:42,900
你怎么知道我在军队服过役?
How do you know about my time in the army?

551
00:33:43,900 --> 00:33:46,168
请原谅 威斯顿先生 
Forgive me, Mr Weston. 

552
00:33:46,169 --> 00:33:48,890
军旅生涯一直是我所向往的
Military history is a passion of mine.

553
00:33:48,900 --> 00:33:52,890
印度兵变真是个野蛮的行动
The Indian Mutiny was a barbaric business

554
00:33:52,900 --> 00:33:57,395
对我来说 能坐在一个经历了那战役的人 
and for me to find myself sitting next to a man 

555
00:33:57,396 --> 00:34:01,890
指挥战斗 因为英勇而授勋的人身边...
who was there, an officer who led the fight, was decorated for his courage...

556
00:34:01,900 --> 00:34:05,900
能为您这样的人服务是我莫大的荣幸 先生
it would be a great honour to serve you in any way you consider, sir.

557
00:34:07,900 --> 00:34:11,890
密切监视莫里
Keep a watch on Moray.

558
00:34:11,900 --> 00:34:12,900
弄清楚他在密谋什么
Find out what he is contriving.

559
00:34:18,900 --> 00:34:21,890
您选的这只真是太棒了 真惹人注目
Ah, it's a wonderful piece you've chosen. Spectacular.

560
00:34:21,900 --> 00:34:23,900
那么 慢走 谢谢
Well, enjoy and thank you.

561
00:34:27,900 --> 00:34:29,890
我们今晚一起出去吗?
Shall we walk out tonight?

562
00:34:29,900 --> 00:34:32,890
或许我们都会去三冠酒店
Aye, we'll probably all go over to The Three Crowns, I suppose.

563
00:34:32,900 --> 00:34:36,900
不 我没说所有人 我是说就你和我
Well, no, I don't mean all. I mean just you and me.

564
00:34:37,900 --> 00:34:39,938
苏西 关于那只表的所有小把戏 
Susy, all that carry on with the watch,

565
00:34:39,939 --> 00:34:40,890
都只是开玩笑的
 it was just a lark.

566
00:34:40,900 --> 00:34:42,890
你真是个英俊的野兽
You're such a handsome beast.

567
00:34:42,900 --> 00:34:46,890
苏西 催眠术只不过是个笑话
Susy. Hypnosis - it's nothing more than a joke.

568
00:34:46,900 --> 00:34:48,890
那只表也没有任何力量 它只是一只表
That watch has no power. It's just a watch.

569
00:34:48,900 --> 00:34:52,890
- 你用它来看时间而已 - 我爱上你了 
- You tell the time with it. - I could fall for a lad like you.

570
00:34:52,900 --> 00:34:56,890
我能说 慢点 你没有爱上我 什么都没发生
Can I just say, slow down? You're not in love with me. Nothing happened.

571
00:34:56,900 --> 00:34:58,890
也许你觉得发生了什么
You might think that something happened

572
00:34:58,900 --> 00:35:02,890
但那只是因为 你就是这样的人
but that's just because, well, it's the kind of person you are.

573
00:35:02,900 --> 00:35:05,895
所以如果你能仔细想想 
So if you could just get it into your mind 

574
00:35:05,896 --> 00:35:08,890
那只表并没有让你爱上我
that that watch did not make you fall in love with me.

575
00:35:08,900 --> 00:35:11,900
达德利先生来了 你最好赶快回你的部门
Oh, there's Mr Dudley, you'd better get back to your department.

576
00:35:12,900 --> 00:35:14,900
- 晚上见 - 好的
- See you tonight. - Sure.

577
00:35:20,900 --> 00:35:22,900
能否给我来杯茶 梅尔托?
Any chance of a cup of tea, Myrtle?

578
00:35:24,900 --> 00:35:25,890
我今晚真不敢去酒吧了
I daren't go to the pub tonight.

579
00:35:25,900 --> 00:35:29,890
苏西好像把那个该死的催眠当真了
Susy seems to think that that damned hypnotism was real.

580
00:35:29,900 --> 00:35:31,259
她一直对我暗送秋波 
She keeps making eyes at me 

581
00:35:31,260 --> 00:35:32,890
像个忠实的小狗一样缠着我
and pestering me like a devoted puppy.

582
00:35:32,900 --> 00:35:34,890
山姆 你正是我要的人
Oh, Sam, you're just the lad I need.

583
00:35:34,900 --> 00:35:37,890
威斯顿先生让我为美食厅做点特别的
Mr Weston has asked me to do something special for the Food Hall

584
00:35:37,900 --> 00:35:39,890
但我的脑子里一点概念都没有
and there's not a notion in my head.

585
00:35:39,900 --> 00:35:42,038
我不是厨子 梅尔托 
I'm no cook, Myrtle. 

586
00:35:42,039 --> 00:35:44,890
不 但你可以用你的表给我催眠
No, but you could mesmerise me with the watch

587
00:35:44,900 --> 00:35:46,890
那么也许我会突发灵感
so that something might appear.

588
00:35:46,900 --> 00:35:48,608
我不是说了吗? 那是胡说八道的 
Didn't I just say? It's nonsense.

589
00:35:48,609 --> 00:35:50,943
我都是装的 那只是个笑话 哈哈! 
 I was pretending. It was a joke. Ha-ha!

590
00:35:50,944 --> 00:35:53,900
是的 我知道 但你能不能试试?
Yes, I know that. But will you try?

591
00:35:54,900 --> 00:35:56,900
你好 山姆
Hello, Sam.

592
00:36:13,900 --> 00:36:17,890
德妮丝 你的演讲真让人大受鼓舞
Denise, your presentation was quite an inspiration.

593
00:36:17,900 --> 00:36:20,890
- 每个人都在谈论你 - 谢谢 先生
- Everyone is talking about it. - Thank you, sir.

594
00:36:20,900 --> 00:36:25,890
我突然想到或许你应该在每个部门都呆一天
Yes. It occurs to me that you might spend a day in each department,

595
00:36:25,900 --> 00:36:29,890
给他们注入从你身上散发出来的那种生活乐趣
infuse them with that joie de vivre that seems to spill out of you.

596
00:36:29,900 --> 00:36:31,890
呃 先生 我们实施政策之前
Er, isn't this something we ought to discuss

597
00:36:31,900 --> 00:36:35,890
不应该先讨论一下吗?
before implementing policy on the hoof, sir?

598
00:36:35,900 --> 00:36:37,890
以我的经验来说 经营一家商场
In my experience of running a store,

599
00:36:37,900 --> 00:36:39,890
这种决策应该先在管理层中讨论过
one must consider such things amongst management

600
00:36:39,900 --> 00:36:42,890
再通知员工
before speaking to the staff. 

601
00:36:42,900 --> 00:36:44,475
你怎么想的 德妮丝? 
What do you think, Denise? 

602
00:36:44,476 --> 00:36:46,900
- 先生 能否... - 不能 德妮丝?
- Sir, if I may... - You may not. Denise?

603
00:36:47,900 --> 00:36:50,890
这不是我能决定的 先生
It is not for me to decide, sir.

604
00:36:50,900 --> 00:36:53,900
我不是在让你决定 我是在问你的意见
I'm not asking you to decide. I'm asking for your opinion.

605
00:36:56,900 --> 00:37:00,890
我可以的 先生 当然要其他部门都同意
It could only work, sir, with the consent of the other departments.

606
00:37:00,900 --> 00:37:03,890
没问题 你可以从厨房开始
Of course. You can start in the kitchens.

607
00:37:03,900 --> 00:37:06,900
我看不出来梅尔托会反对 你呢?
I can't see Myrtle objecting, can you?

608
00:37:17,900 --> 00:37:19,287
只要能找到机会 
Every opportunity he can find

609
00:37:19,288 --> 00:37:21,890
他就对德妮丝大加赞扬并四处推广
 he is lavishing praise and promotion onto Denise.

610
00:37:21,900 --> 00:37:23,890
莫里 你现在比任何时候都要学会控制
Moray, now more than ever you must show restraint.

611
00:37:23,900 --> 00:37:26,890
他仗势欺人 我们都知道他是个怎样的混蛋
He is a bully. We all know what a bully he is.

612
00:37:26,900 --> 00:37:29,890
一个被宠坏的孩子肯定会自行其事
A spoiled child who must have his own way.

613
00:37:29,900 --> 00:37:33,890
我求你 别把事弄大了 别密谋反对他
I implore you, do not rise to this. Do not scheme against him.

614
00:37:33,900 --> 00:37:35,890
我不会让他弄垮我的
I will not let him crush me.

615
00:37:35,900 --> 00:37:37,728
我知道 你在谋画些什么
You're up to something. I know it. 

616
00:37:37,729 --> 00:37:39,890
为什么你不告诉我...?
Why won't you tell me...?

617
00:37:39,900 --> 00:37:41,890
达德利 相信我 我知道我在做什么
Dudley, just trust that I know what I'm doing.

618
00:37:41,900 --> 00:37:44,890
我不能 忠诚不是条单行道
I cannot. Loyalty is not a one-way track.

619
00:37:44,900 --> 00:37:47,890
我试图鼓励你来告诉我到底发生了什么
I have tried to encourage you to tell me what is going on.

620
00:37:47,900 --> 00:37:50,890
你拒绝了 也就是说你不信任我
You refuse. That means you do not trust me.

621
00:37:50,900 --> 00:37:51,616
达德利... 
Dudley... 

622
00:37:51,617 --> 00:37:53,890
你还把希望都寄托于乔纳斯
Yet you choose to lay your faith in Jonas.

623
00:37:53,900 --> 00:37:54,900
这是为了我们大家都好
It's for the good of all of us.

624
00:37:55,900 --> 00:37:58,900
那为什么我从你脸上看到的不是这样?
Then why is that not what I see in your face?

625
00:38:04,900 --> 00:38:08,890
你来主管? 我的厨房?
In charge? You? My kitchen?

626
00:38:08,900 --> 00:38:11,890
不是主管 不是
Not in charge, no.

627
00:38:11,900 --> 00:38:15,900
就一天而已 也许我们在一起会很开心
Simply, for one day, we might have some fun together.

628
00:38:17,900 --> 00:38:20,890
如果你不愿意我不会这样做的 梅尔托
I don't wish to do this if you don't want me here, Myrtle.

629
00:38:20,900 --> 00:38:23,900
如果一天变成了两天呢 然后呢
What if one day becomes two? What then?

630
00:38:24,900 --> 00:38:28,890
威斯顿先生想要一份橱窗展品
Mr Weston wants a display for the window.

631
00:38:28,900 --> 00:38:31,890
我觉得... 梅尔托蛋糕最好
I thought... Myrtle Cake.

632
00:38:31,900 --> 00:38:34,038
梅尔托蛋糕? 
Myrtle Cake? 

633
00:38:34,039 --> 00:38:36,890
你的食谱 十八个鸡蛋
Your recipe. Eighteen eggs.

634
00:38:36,900 --> 00:38:39,890
我可以装饰一边的窗户 还有鸡
We could decorate the window at one end, chickens.

635
00:38:39,900 --> 00:38:41,890
活鸡 用玉米喂它们
Live chickens, feeding on corn.

636
00:38:41,900 --> 00:38:44,890
第二层摆上堆积如山的鸡蛋
And next to that a mountain of eggs.

637
00:38:44,900 --> 00:38:49,900
然后 在漂亮的展台上的就是 梅尔托蛋糕
And then, on a beautiful stand - Myrtle Cake.

638
00:38:50,900 --> 00:38:52,890
梅尔托蛋糕
Myrtle Cake.

639
00:38:52,900 --> 00:38:55,890
你可以用各种糖果和装饰来美化它
You could decorate it with all manner of sweets and ornaments.

640
00:38:55,900 --> 00:38:57,890
我们也许可以
We might sell the recipe.

641
00:38:57,900 --> 00:38:59,890
向买蛋糕的顾客售卖食谱
And for those customers who buy the cake,

642
00:38:59,900 --> 00:39:01,496
他们可以来你的厨房 
they could come into your kitchen 

643
00:39:01,497 --> 00:39:03,890
听你是如何学到做这个蛋糕的故事
and hear your tales of how you learned to make the cake.

644
00:39:03,900 --> 00:39:06,466
你告诉威斯顿先生这个主意了吗? 
Did you tell Mr Weston this idea? 

645
00:39:06,467 --> 00:39:08,890
- 还没有 - 我们可以一起告诉他
- Not yet. - We might tell him together.

646
00:39:08,900 --> 00:39:10,802
过来 如果你想在我的厨房工作
Here! If you're going to be working in my kitchen 

647
00:39:10,803 --> 00:39:11,890
你需要一条围裙
you'll need an apron.

648
00:39:11,900 --> 00:39:14,890
你知道我们要放什么在梅尔托蛋糕里吗?
You know what we might put in this Myrtle Cake?

649
00:39:14,900 --> 00:39:18,900
柠檬 蜜糖和姜来给蛋糕一点梅尔托的味道
Lemon and treacle and ginger to give it that bit of Myrtle spice!

650
00:39:20,900 --> 00:39:22,890
忙着掌控世界啊 德妮丝
So busy taking over the world, Denise,

651
00:39:22,900 --> 00:39:25,890
你应该认真确定你没有错过真正重要的部分
you ought to be careful you don't miss out what really matters.

652
00:39:25,900 --> 00:39:27,852
你什么意思? 
What do you mean? 

653
00:39:27,853 --> 00:39:30,890
你那么喜欢这个 不是吗?
Well, you love it all so much, don't you?

654
00:39:30,900 --> 00:39:32,850
他们可以把你放在店里的任何角落
They could drop you anywhere in the store, 

655
00:39:32,851 --> 00:39:33,890
城市的任何地方
anywhere in the city,

656
00:39:33,900 --> 00:39:35,890
然后你让事情按着你的方式来
and you would make it sing to your tune.

657
00:39:35,900 --> 00:39:38,890
- 那又怎么样呢? - 没什么
- What's wrong with that? - Nothing.

658
00:39:38,900 --> 00:39:41,890
确实那样没什么不对的
There is really nothing wrong with that.

659
00:39:41,900 --> 00:39:43,900
你想对我说什么 克莱拉?
What are you trying to say to me, Clara?

660
00:39:44,900 --> 00:39:45,890
朋友们尝试警告我
Friends tried to warn me

661
00:39:45,900 --> 00:39:48,890
我生活的方式会赶上我
the way I lived me life would catch up with me

662
00:39:48,900 --> 00:39:50,890
但是我必须自己领会
but I had to learn it for myself.

663
00:39:50,900 --> 00:39:53,900
也许我们都需要自己领会
Perhaps we all have to learn it for ourselves.

664
00:39:58,900 --> 00:40:02,890
山姆 我听说我父亲的手表曾引起轰动
I hear my father's watch has caused something of a stir, Sam.

665
00:40:02,900 --> 00:40:06,890
夫人 我会说 这比轰动更厉害
More of a splash than a stir, I would say, ma'am.

666
00:40:06,900 --> 00:40:10,890
我想请问你 当你告诉我们这个手表...
Might I ask when you told us about the watch,

667
00:40:10,900 --> 00:40:12,890
那个... 催眠术
you know, the hypnotism

668
00:40:12,900 --> 00:40:15,890
还有你父亲在你小时候给你施法的事情
and your father saying that as a child he could put you under his spell,

669
00:40:15,900 --> 00:40:18,890
那都是开玩笑吗?
that was all jest?

670
00:40:18,900 --> 00:40:21,890
当然啦 我父亲很会说笑
Yes, of course. My father was quite the tease.

671
00:40:21,900 --> 00:40:23,890
正如我所想的
That's what I thought.

672
00:40:23,900 --> 00:40:26,890
他只是骗骗我而已
He was fooling with me, that's all.

673
00:40:26,900 --> 00:40:29,890
但是 有一次他说服了我
Except, there was that one time he convinced me

674
00:40:29,900 --> 00:40:32,890
在手表的影响下我说了外语
that under the influence of the watch I had spoken a foreign language.

675
00:40:32,900 --> 00:40:34,762
我想是希腊语 
Greek, I believe. 

676
00:40:34,763 --> 00:40:38,900
- 希腊语? - 是啊 但是真的很有趣
- Greek? - Yes, but it was all rather good fun.

677
00:40:39,900 --> 00:40:43,890
确实有一件事让我感到惊讶
There was that one incident that did rather astonish me.

678
00:40:43,900 --> 00:40:46,890
小时候 我不爱吃卷心菜
As a child, I refused to eat cabbage,

679
00:40:46,900 --> 00:40:49,890
但是有一次
yet on one occasion,

680
00:40:49,900 --> 00:40:52,890
我父亲在饭桌上拿手表在我眼前晃
my father dangled the watch in front of me at the dinner table

681
00:40:52,900 --> 00:40:55,890
然后我吃了很多卷心菜 也没有抱怨
and I ate a plateful without complaint.

682
00:40:55,900 --> 00:40:58,890
- 卷心菜? - 我甚至乐在其中
- Cabbage? - I rather enjoyed it, too.

683
00:40:58,900 --> 00:41:03,890
- 我想孩子总是乐于接受建议的 - 是的
- I suppose a child's mind is open to suggestion. - Yes. That's it.

684
00:41:03,900 --> 00:41:07,890
有一个关于做这个手表的人的神秘故事
Oh, and there was such a mystery about the watchmaker who made it.

685
00:41:07,900 --> 00:41:10,890
他左手似乎有六个手指
He had six fingers on his left hand, apparently.

686
00:41:10,900 --> 00:41:13,890
他还能看到未来
And he could see into the future.

687
00:41:13,900 --> 00:41:16,890
我父亲喜欢跟我说这些故事
My father loved to tell me these stories.

688
00:41:16,900 --> 00:41:19,900
那些故事总让我吓坏了
They used to frighten the life out of me.

689
00:41:20,900 --> 00:41:22,900
六个手指
Six fingers.

690
00:41:27,900 --> 00:41:29,890
失陪了 先生
Excuse me a moment, sir.

691
00:41:29,900 --> 00:41:31,574
你肯定会觉得我一直在关注传家宝 
You will think I am keeping an eye on the family heirloom, 

692
00:41:31,575 --> 00:41:32,890
我来得太勤了
I'm in here so often.

693
00:41:32,900 --> 00:41:34,900
完全没有 很高兴见到你
Not at all. It's a pleasure to see you.

694
00:41:36,900 --> 00:41:38,900
实际上 我想...
In truth, I wanted to...

695
00:41:39,900 --> 00:41:42,890
我想我那天说了太多了
I think I said rather too much the other day.

696
00:41:42,900 --> 00:41:45,890
不不不 我很高兴我们聊天了 凯瑟琳
No, no, no, no. I'm glad that we spoke, Katherine.

697
00:41:45,900 --> 00:41:50,890
我很高兴知道我们之间的感情没有消失
It has eased my mind to know that the fondness between us is not lost.

698
00:41:50,900 --> 00:41:53,900
我也这么觉得
Yes. I feel the same way.

699
00:41:55,900 --> 00:42:00,125
如果像我们之前那样亲密的两个人之间有敌意
When two people have been as close as we were, - then it hurts too much for

700
00:42:00,126 --> 00:42:01,900
- 那就太伤人了 - 是啊
- there to be any ill will. - Yes.

701
00:42:03,900 --> 00:42:08,900
也许我们可以时常聚聚喝杯咖啡
Perhaps we could meet from time to time, for coffee?

702
00:42:09,900 --> 00:42:13,900
- 我很乐意 - 那我们一定要聚聚
- I would like that. - Well, then, we must.

703
00:42:14,900 --> 00:42:18,890
也许... 汤姆有时候会无理地嫉妒
Perhaps... Tom can be so unreasonably jealous sometimes,

704
00:42:18,900 --> 00:42:20,900
所以不要让他知道
it would be unhelpful for him to know.

705
00:42:21,900 --> 00:42:26,900
如果你希望这样 那我当然会尊重你的意愿
If that is what you prefer, then, of course, I will respect your wishes.

706
00:42:39,900 --> 00:42:43,900
莫里 你愿意和我还有我妻子一起共进晚餐吗
Moray! Would you be so kind as to join my wife and I for dinner?

707
00:42:45,900 --> 00:42:47,890
如果你希望的话
If you wish, sir.

708
00:42:47,900 --> 00:42:52,900
我是说 我很高兴你邀请我 我有一点意外
What I mean is, I am grateful for the invitation, if a little surprised.

709
00:42:54,900 --> 00:42:55,890
我有一些消息
I have some news.

710
00:42:55,900 --> 00:42:58,890
好消息最好是伴着香槟酒到来
Good news is always best delivered with a glass of champagne.

711
00:42:58,900 --> 00:43:01,890
对我来说是好消息吗 你让我好奇了
Good news for me? You have me curious, sir.

712
00:43:01,900 --> 00:43:03,718
这好消息是给德妮丝的 
The news is for Denise. 

713
00:43:03,719 --> 00:43:05,900
是你来邀请她还是我来?
Will you invite her or shall I?

714
00:43:30,900 --> 00:43:33,900
你好 山姆
Hello, Sam.

715
00:43:34,900 --> 00:43:37,900
我得赶回店里
I've just got to run back to the store.

716
00:43:41,900 --> 00:43:44,890
他有消息为什么不直接告诉我们呢?
If he has news, then why doesn't he simply tell us?

717
00:43:44,900 --> 00:43:46,890
为什么邀请我们去他家?
Why invite us to the house?

718
00:43:46,900 --> 00:43:49,890
想到和他们共进晚餐就苦恼
The thought of dinner with them is excruciating.

719
00:43:49,900 --> 00:43:52,890
你自己说的 我们必须和他们保持良好的关系
You said yourself, we must keep good relations with them

720
00:43:52,900 --> 00:43:53,890
这正是我们现在在做的
and that is what we are doing.

721
00:43:53,900 --> 00:43:58,890
- 我不相信他 - 我想他也不相信你
- I don't trust him. - I don't suppose he trusts you either.

722
00:43:58,900 --> 00:44:00,118
你是什么意思呢? 
What do you mean? 

723
00:44:00,119 --> 00:44:01,890
他知道你想要把天堂百货拿回来
He knows you want The Paradise back

724
00:44:01,900 --> 00:44:03,694
你在千方百计达到你的目的  
and that you are looking for ways to do that. 

725
00:44:03,695 --> 00:44:04,890
我们必须谨慎 德妮丝
We must be wary, Denise.

726
00:44:04,900 --> 00:44:07,890
不管是什么消息 其中肯定有陷阱
Whatever this news is, there will be a trap in it.

727
00:44:07,900 --> 00:44:11,890
约翰 也许这个晚上是向他们证明
John, perhaps this evening is an opportunity to prove to them

728
00:44:11,900 --> 00:44:14,890
我们很融洽的机会
how devoted we are to one another

729
00:44:14,900 --> 00:44:17,900
我们一起就不用害怕他们
and that together we're not afraid of them.

730
00:44:18,900 --> 00:44:21,900
是的
Yes.

731
00:44:22,900 --> 00:44:24,890
晚餐? 这里? 他们两个人?
Dinner? Here? The two of them?

732
00:44:24,900 --> 00:44:27,890
- 我想一定会很有趣 - 你应该先问问我
- I thought it might be rather fun. - You might have asked me.

733
00:44:27,900 --> 00:44:31,588
也许你和莫里在众目睽睽之下
And you might have asked me before you took to 

734
00:44:31,589 --> 00:44:32,890
沿着托尔盖特街散步之前
promenading along Tollgate Street with Moray,

735
00:44:32,900 --> 00:44:35,890
- 也应该先问问我 - 我明白了
- for all the world to gaze upon and wonder. - I see.

736
00:44:35,900 --> 00:44:40,900
我了解到 在那个职位上 她有很强的欲望
I have learnt by being about that place that she has quite an appetite.

737
00:44:41,900 --> 00:44:46,890
德妮丝很有野心 我很乐意去培养她
Denise is bubbling with ambition. It pleases me to foster that.

738
00:44:47,900 --> 00:44:49,900
她所有的表现都比他更出色
She shows every sign of outshining him.

739
00:44:51,900 --> 00:44:53,900
莫里也许不是适合她的男人
Moray may prove to be not man enough for her.

740
00:44:54,900 --> 00:44:57,900
我喜欢在这里招待她这个主意
I like the idea of entertaining her here.

741
00:44:58,900 --> 00:45:02,900
我猜她会喜欢烛光闪闪的晚餐
I suspect she will have a taste for a little glitter.

742
00:45:03,900 --> 00:45:07,900
正如我说的 威斯顿先生在战斗中受伤了
Mr Weston, as I suggested to you, sir, was injured in battle.

743
00:45:03,900 --> 00:45:07,900
"退役军官因战斗英勇获维多利亚十字勋章"

744
00:45:08,900 --> 00:45:10,890
恐怕伤得很严重
Hurt badly it would seem.

745
00:45:10,900 --> 00:45:13,890
从印度回来 从军队退役
Returned home from India, retired from the army.

746
00:45:13,900 --> 00:45:15,900
那是否就可以解释...?
Then might that not explain...?

747
00:45:18,900 --> 00:45:20,890
汤姆・威斯顿为他的国家效力
Tom Weston was serving his country

748
00:45:20,900 --> 00:45:23,890
我却在这里卖最新的时尚品
while I was here selling the latest fashions.

749
00:45:23,900 --> 00:45:26,900
难怪他对我这样的人有怨恨
Is it any wonder he holds a grudge against men like me?

750
00:45:29,900 --> 00:45:33,890
他已经遭受了远超我想象的痛苦
Is it not shameful of us to inflict further turmoil

751
00:45:33,900 --> 00:45:38,890
我们还对要对付他 不是很可耻吗?
on the soldier who's suffered beyond anything I can imagine?

752
00:45:38,900 --> 00:45:40,900
如果你可怜他 你就永远不能打败他
If you pity the man you will never defeat him.

753
00:45:41,900 --> 00:45:44,890
先生 恕我直言
Sir, if I may.

754
00:45:44,900 --> 00:45:46,890
威斯顿先生必须知道那只手表的事
Mr Weston must learn about the watch, sir.

755
00:45:46,900 --> 00:45:50,890
我能找到机会告诉他
I can find an opportunity to present him with the knowledge

756
00:45:50,900 --> 00:45:53,890
他的妻子向他隐瞒了她父亲的意愿
that his wife has concealed from him her father's intentions.

757
00:45:53,900 --> 00:45:56,940
不 乔纳斯 别在我读了这个之后这么做 
No, Jonas. Not after reading this. 

758
00:45:56,941 --> 00:45:57,900
我不想他知道
I don't want him to know.

759
00:45:59,900 --> 00:46:02,890
我告诉你 艾德蒙 我没有把它放进口袋
I tell you, Edmund. I didn't put it in my pocket.

760
00:46:02,900 --> 00:46:05,890
但是你一定把它放在那儿了 你只是忘记了
But you must have put it there. You've forgotten.

761
00:46:05,900 --> 00:46:07,890
这就更糟糕了
That's worse, isn't it?

762
00:46:07,900 --> 00:46:10,890
我把它放进自己的口袋却都不知道
I put it in my own pocket and I didn't even realise I was doing it?

763
00:46:10,900 --> 00:46:12,890
就好像手表自己走到那里的一样
It's like the watch put itself there.

764
00:46:12,900 --> 00:46:15,900
- 山姆 这对话太疯狂了 - 那手表
- Sam, lad, this is wild talk. - That thing.

765
00:46:17,900 --> 00:46:21,890
对了 有个在海湾工作的家伙
Right, there's this fella who works in the bay

766
00:46:21,900 --> 00:46:24,890
李 雷蒙德・李 李跳蚤
Lee, Raymond Lee. Lee the Flea.

767
00:46:24,900 --> 00:46:25,890
我从来都不喜欢那个家伙
I never liked the bloke

768
00:46:25,900 --> 00:46:28,890
他昨天一直对我喋喋不休
and he was rattling on me yesterday, on and on.

769
00:46:28,900 --> 00:46:30,890
我站在我的柜台 我脑子里在想咒语
I'm standing at my counter, I'm cursing in my head.

770
00:46:30,900 --> 00:46:33,890
今天 你猜怎么着 他生病在床上了
Now today, what do you think? He's taken sick to his bed.

771
00:46:33,900 --> 00:46:35,070
怎么会这样? 
How does that happen? 

772
00:46:35,071 --> 00:46:36,890
那是因为有时候人们会生病
It happens because sometimes people get ill.

773
00:46:36,900 --> 00:46:39,890
不不
No, no.

774
00:46:39,900 --> 00:46:42,890
是那手表 我知道的
It's the watch. I know it is.

775
00:46:42,900 --> 00:46:45,890
苏西像狗皮膏药一样一直绕着我转
I've got Susy following me around like a sop.

776
00:46:45,900 --> 00:46:47,890
我怎么也甩不掉她
I can't shake her out of it no matter what I do.

777
00:46:47,900 --> 00:46:49,890
如果这让你那么烦恼
Well, if it's bothering you that much,

778
00:46:49,900 --> 00:46:51,900
你为什么不叫达德利先生把你调离手表柜台呢
why don't you ask Mr Dudley to take you off the watch counter?

779
00:46:53,900 --> 00:46:55,890
我会的
I will. I will.

780
00:46:55,900 --> 00:46:57,900
就... 就这么办
That's... That's what I'll do.

781
00:47:16,900 --> 00:47:19,890
太值得称赞了 对吧莫里
It is so laudable, is it not, Moray,

782
00:47:19,900 --> 00:47:23,890
一个女孩从一个小镇来
for a girl to come from a lowly little town like...

783
00:47:23,900 --> 00:47:26,900
- 是哪里 德妮丝 - 先生 是皮布尔斯
- Where is it, Denise? - Peebles, sir.

784
00:47:27,900 --> 00:47:31,900
皮布尔斯 甚至连名字读起来都是一种款待
Peebles. Even the word is a treat on the tongue.

785
00:47:33,900 --> 00:47:37,890
我和凯瑟琳都难以想象 从小城镇到大城市
Katherine and I have no idea what it means to come from such beginnings

786
00:47:37,900 --> 00:47:40,890
并在大城市证明自己 意味着什么
and to prove oneself in the city.

787
00:47:40,900 --> 00:47:41,890
我想这不亚于
I suppose it's no small feat

788
00:47:41,900 --> 00:47:44,890
想在军队里证明自己 威斯顿先生
to prove oneself in the armed forces, Mr Weston.

789
00:47:44,900 --> 00:47:47,890
是啊 很恰当的比喻
Yes. There is that.

790
00:47:47,900 --> 00:47:49,420
但对于一个女人 
But for a woman, 

791
00:47:49,421 --> 00:47:51,890
一个年轻的女人在男人的世界
a young woman in a man's world,

792
00:47:51,900 --> 00:47:54,890
打拼 满怀着...
and to do it all with such...

793
00:47:54,900 --> 00:47:58,890
那叫什么 莫里?
What shall we call it, Moray?

794
00:47:58,900 --> 00:48:01,890
- 渴望? - 哦 不!
- Eagerness? - Oh, come!

795
00:48:01,900 --> 00:48:05,900
这不是我所想的 我想说满怀着这样的热情
That is not what I meant at all. I mean with such effervescence.

796
00:48:11,900 --> 00:48:13,890
我们想知道是什么消息 先生
We were wondering what the news might be, sir.

797
00:48:13,900 --> 00:48:17,371
他庆幸过自己的幸运吗 德妮丝? 
Does he appreciate what a fortunate man he is, Denise? 

798
00:48:17,372 --> 00:48:18,890
我希望他庆幸过
I hope he does.

799
00:48:18,900 --> 00:48:21,890
他有过 而且我也很庆幸能跟约翰一起工作
Yes. And I am very fortunate to work with John.

800
00:48:21,900 --> 00:48:23,890
他经常鼓励我
He's always encouraged me.

801
00:48:23,900 --> 00:48:25,723
是吗 莫里? 
Do you, Moray? 

802
00:48:25,724 --> 00:48:29,890
知道你身边的女人有多优秀吗?
Do you realise quite what a woman you have on your hands?

803
00:48:29,900 --> 00:48:31,900
不知道我就是傻瓜了 先生
I'd be a fool not to, sir.

804
00:48:33,900 --> 00:48:35,900
我是有消息
News indeed.

805
00:48:36,900 --> 00:48:40,890
我们想送你去巴黎 德妮丝
We want to send you to Paris, Denise.

806
00:48:40,900 --> 00:48:42,890
这是一个考察任务
On a reconnaissance mission.

807
00:48:42,900 --> 00:48:44,890
你去探访乐蓬马歇百货
To visit Le Bon Marche

808
00:48:44,900 --> 00:48:47,890
了解最新的法国时尚
and to fill your eyes with the latest French fashions.

809
00:48:47,900 --> 00:48:51,900
是吗! 这真是太...
Well! That is rather...

810
00:48:52,900 --> 00:48:54,890
我不知道该说什么
I don't quite know what to say.

811
00:48:54,900 --> 00:48:55,890
谢谢!
Thank you!

812
00:48:55,900 --> 00:49:00,890
一周的时间 你就尽情享受巴黎的时尚吧
Spend a week there. Immerse yourself in all things Parisienne.

813
00:49:01,900 --> 00:49:06,890
我希望我们女装部的主管能深入了解插画时尚
We want our Head of Ladieswear to be versed in La Mode Illustree.

814
00:49:01,890 --> 00:49:06,890
插画时尚: 法国第一本主要的时尚杂志

815
00:49:06,900 --> 00:49:09,890
你觉得自己可以出行吗?
Do you think you are ready for such a trip?

816
00:49:09,900 --> 00:49:11,900
是的 先生
Yes, sir.

817
00:49:12,900 --> 00:49:14,900
德妮丝在巴黎!
Denise in Paris!

818
00:49:20,900 --> 00:49:22,890
你知道他对我们做了什么吗? 亲爱的
'Don't you see what he is doing to us, darling?'

819
00:49:22,900 --> 00:49:25,890
他在给你奖赏 你却欣然接受了
He's feeding you with prizes so that you feel happy here,

820
00:49:25,900 --> 00:49:28,890
你遵照了他的想法
so that you accept the way things are.

821
00:49:28,900 --> 00:49:30,890
去巴黎我能学到很多
I could learn so much in Paris.

822
00:49:30,900 --> 00:49:33,890
我不是想阻止你
It's not that I want to stop you from going.

823
00:49:33,900 --> 00:49:35,900
只是想让你意识到他干了什么
I want you to see what he's doing.

824
00:49:38,900 --> 00:49:40,890
我会想办法拒绝他
I'll find a reason to say no.

825
00:49:40,900 --> 00:49:45,890
跟他说我生病了 或是这次出行会让我生病
I'll tell him I'm sick or that the travelling will make me ill.

826
00:49:46,900 --> 00:49:49,890
这都是为了我们好 德妮丝
It is for us that I am doing this, Denise,

827
00:49:49,900 --> 00:49:51,900
为了我们能一起在天堂百货
so we can be together in The Paradise.

828
00:49:54,900 --> 00:49:55,900
我明白
I know.

829
00:50:16,900 --> 00:50:19,890
我一直想做台前的工作
I always wanted it to be me out front

830
00:50:19,900 --> 00:50:21,938
但现在我的点心替我受到关注
but it feels better for it to be my baking 

831
00:50:21,939 --> 00:50:22,890
让我更开心
what's in the limelight.

832
00:50:22,900 --> 00:50:24,900
谢谢你 德妮丝
Thank you, Denise.

833
00:50:30,100 --> 00:50:31,900
"梅尔托蛋糕"

834
00:50:38,900 --> 00:50:40,890
达德利先生 请您批准 先生
Mr Dudley, sir, with your permission, sir,

835
00:50:40,900 --> 00:50:42,890
我想调离怀表柜台
I would like to be taken off the watch counter.

836
00:50:42,900 --> 00:50:44,890
但怀表是我们的畅销品之一
But the watches are our best-selling item.

837
00:50:44,900 --> 00:50:45,752
你在创造奇迹 
You're working wonders. 

838
00:50:45,753 --> 00:50:46,890
但是 如果您能批准 先生
But still, if you will, sir.

839
00:50:46,900 --> 00:50:48,890
我会很感激
I'd appreciate the move.

840
00:50:48,900 --> 00:50:51,890
你从没赚过那么多奖金 为什么不做呢
You've never earned so much bonus. Why would you turn your back on that?

841
00:50:51,900 --> 00:50:55,890
卖怀表不适合我 我宁愿回去卖丝绸
Watches aren't for me. I prefer to go back to silks.

842
00:50:55,900 --> 00:50:56,896
我会考虑看看 
I'll give it some thought. 

843
00:50:56,897 --> 00:51:01,890
您能现在就考虑吗? 您就站在这儿
Could you give it some thought now, sir, while you're standing here?

844
00:51:01,900 --> 00:51:05,890
如果职员都随意调来调去 会影响不好
It creates a bad impression if staff are hopping about from counter to counter.

845
00:51:05,900 --> 00:51:07,890
我希望你能继续工作
I want you to see it through with the watches.

846
00:51:07,900 --> 00:51:12,890
- 要是我恳求您呢? 先生 - 为什么?
- If I were to plead with you sir? - But for what reason?

847
00:51:12,900 --> 00:51:15,900
给我个合理的理由 我会考虑看看
Give me a sound reason and I will give it some consideration.

848
00:51:18,900 --> 00:51:19,900
那好吧 达德利先生
Very well, Mr Dudley, sir.

849
00:51:34,900 --> 00:51:36,900
进来
Come in.

850
00:51:40,900 --> 00:51:42,890
我要你告诉他
I want you to tell him.

851
00:51:42,900 --> 00:51:44,070
告诉汤姆・威斯顿 
Tell Tom Weston that 

852
00:51:44,071 --> 00:51:45,890
格伦德宁勋爵打算把自己的怀表
Lord Glendenning intended his watch

853
00:51:45,900 --> 00:51:49,900
传给凯瑟琳的丈夫 但她隐瞒了他
to be left to Katherine's husband but she's kept this from him.

854
00:52:02,900 --> 00:52:05,890
你还在卖那些表吗?
You're still doing the watches then?

855
00:52:05,900 --> 00:52:08,890
我请求达德利先生将我们调走 但他拒绝了
I asked Mr Dudley to move us but he refused.

856
00:52:08,900 --> 00:52:11,890
看那表 挂在那儿像是在嘲笑我们
Look at it. Hangs there like it's mocking us.

857
00:52:11,900 --> 00:52:14,890
山姆 你得冷静 你要失去理智了
Sam, you need to calm down. You're letting your mind run away with you.

858
00:52:14,900 --> 00:52:16,890
那玩意儿还在那儿 你让我怎么冷静?
How can I calm down when the thing's right there?

859
00:52:16,900 --> 00:52:18,075
它要禁锢我们 我恨它 
It wants to possess us. - I hate it. 

860
00:52:18,076 --> 00:52:18,890
山姆 别说了!
Sam, stop it!

861
00:52:18,900 --> 00:52:21,890
我有种冲动 想把它扔进河里
I'm getting such urges in my mind, hat I want to throw it in the river,

862
00:52:21,900 --> 00:52:23,890
走上桥 放进包里 外加一颗石头
go down to the bridge, put it in a bag with a stone

863
00:52:23,900 --> 00:52:25,890
然后扔进水里 摆脱它
and toss it into the water, be rid of it.

864
00:52:25,900 --> 00:52:27,890
然后我可能会恢复平静
Then I might be at peace again.

865
00:52:27,900 --> 00:52:29,890
山姆 一旦你这么做 你将在监狱度过余生
Sam, if you do that you'll end up in prison.

866
00:52:29,900 --> 00:52:32,890
这是块贵重的表 凯瑟琳・威斯顿的表
This is a valuable watch. It's Katherine Weston's watch.

867
00:52:32,900 --> 00:52:35,900
我也不想那么做 但我没法不去想
I don't want to do it. But I can't stop thinking it.

868
00:52:36,900 --> 00:52:39,900
好吧 也许它很快会物归原主 嗯?
Well, perhaps it'll go back where it came from soon, eh?

869
00:52:49,900 --> 00:52:51,900
要跟我喝一杯吗 乔纳斯?
Will you join me in a drink, Jonas?

870
00:52:52,900 --> 00:52:55,890
我... 我得工作了 先生
I... I should be getting on with my duties, sir.

871
00:52:55,900 --> 00:52:59,900
我是你老板 你现在的工作就是和我喝一杯
I'm your employer. Your duty at this moment is to enjoy a drink with me.

872
00:53:02,900 --> 00:53:06,890
你怎么回事?
What's the matter with you?

873
00:53:06,900 --> 00:53:09,890
难道你发现莫里在玩什么鬼把戏了?
Did you find out what Moray is up to?

874
00:53:09,900 --> 00:53:12,900
我没有关于莫里财政的情报 先生
I have no intelligence on Mr Moray's finances, sir.

875
00:53:13,900 --> 00:53:15,900
谨慎说话 乔纳斯
You chose your words too carefully, Jonas.

876
00:53:17,900 --> 00:53:21,890
你在隐瞒我什么?
What are you concealing from me?

877
00:53:21,900 --> 00:53:23,900
你有事 我能看出来
You have something on your mind. I can see it.

878
00:53:24,900 --> 00:53:26,890
这我不能说 先生
It is not for me to tell a man such things, sir.

879
00:53:26,900 --> 00:53:28,890
什么事?
What things?

880
00:53:28,900 --> 00:53:30,900
这很危险 当一个男人意识到... 
It is dangerous when a husband learns...

881
00:53:34,900 --> 00:53:36,900
我妻子?
My wife?

882
00:53:37,900 --> 00:53:39,890
到底是什么 告诉我你所知道的
What is it? I insist you tell me what you know.

883
00:53:39,900 --> 00:53:41,900
- 先生 请别问 - 告诉我
- Please, sir! - Tell me.

884
00:53:45,900 --> 00:53:48,890
那块怀表 先生
The watch, sir.

885
00:53:48,900 --> 00:53:50,893
我看见您的妻子跟莫里在交谈 
I saw your wife talking to Mr Moray. 

886
00:53:50,894 --> 00:53:51,890
怀表怎么了?
What about the watch?

887
00:53:51,900 --> 00:53:55,900
她父亲遗留给她那块表是要传给她的丈夫
Her father bequeathed that the piece was to be passed on to the man she married.

888
00:53:59,900 --> 00:54:02,900
您明白了吧 先生 为什么我不能说
Now you see, sir, why this is impossible for me to tell.

889
00:54:04,900 --> 00:54:06,900
说下去
Carry on.

890
00:54:07,900 --> 00:54:10,890
她决定不告诉你她父亲的遗愿
She has decided not to tell you of her father's wishes.

891
00:54:10,900 --> 00:54:13,890
你听见她跟莫里说这个?
You heard her telling Moray this?

892
00:54:13,900 --> 00:54:17,900
她要求他保密 就他们两人知道
She asked him to keep it a secret, between them.

893
00:54:19,900 --> 00:54:20,900
我明白了
I see.

894
00:54:22,900 --> 00:54:26,030
威斯顿先生 我恐怕不能接受您的好意 
Mr Weston, I'm afraid I can't accept your kind of offer 

895
00:54:26,031 --> 00:54:26,900
去巴黎的事
of a trip to Paris.

896
00:54:30,900 --> 00:54:34,890
我发誓 先生 锁柜台的时候还在的
I promise you, gentlemen. When I closed up my counter it was there.

897
00:54:34,900 --> 00:54:37,890
- 但现在不在了 山姆 - 不是 先生
- But it is not there now, Sam. - No, sir.

898
00:54:37,900 --> 00:54:39,890
我检查过口袋也不在
I've checked my pockets and it's not there.

899
00:54:39,900 --> 00:54:42,890
为什么你会想到检查口袋?
Why would you want to check your pockets?

900
00:54:42,900 --> 00:54:45,890
我 我是说 没错... 很奇怪的 先生
What, what I mean is, right the... The thing is strange, sir.

901
00:54:45,900 --> 00:54:49,890
有天晚上 我知道这难以置信
One night - and I know this is going to be difficult to believe -

902
00:54:49,900 --> 00:54:52,185
我把表收好后 回到房间 
I put it away and I went to my room 

903
00:54:52,186 --> 00:54:53,900
结果表在我的...
and it was, it was in my...

904
00:54:55,900 --> 00:54:59,890
先生 我从没想过拥有那块表
Gentlemen, I have no wish to want that watch.

905
00:54:59,900 --> 00:55:01,890
那该死的表真的着魔了
That damned watch is bewitched.

906
00:55:01,900 --> 00:55:05,900
威斯顿先生拿走了那块表 我看见他拿走了 
Mr Weston took the watch. I saw him take it.

907
00:55:07,900 --> 00:55:09,890
所以它走了
Then it's gone.

908
00:55:09,900 --> 00:55:12,900
我又恢复自由了!
I'm a free man again!

909
00:55:15,900 --> 00:55:17,815
我该怎样阻止她老跟着我 
How do I stop her following me all the time 

910
00:55:17,816 --> 00:55:19,890
注视我犹如我是爱神丘比特?
and looking at me like I'm the God of Love?

911
00:55:19,900 --> 00:55:22,890
还有一见到我就说 "你好 山姆 "?
And saying, "Hello, Sam," every time I see her?

912
00:55:22,900 --> 00:55:24,525
你再给她催眠一次 
You'll have to hypnotise her again. 

913
00:55:24,526 --> 00:55:26,890
我一开始就没给她催眠过
I didn't hypnotise her in the first place.

914
00:55:26,900 --> 00:55:28,890
而且表也还回去了
And the watch is gone now.

915
00:55:28,900 --> 00:55:31,300
就算你告诉苏西你会用鸡毛掸子给她催眠 
Susy would believe it if you told her you'd hypnotised her 

916
00:55:31,301 --> 00:55:31,900
她也会相信
with a feather duster.

917
00:55:33,900 --> 00:55:35,900
让我来吧
Leave it to me.

918
00:55:51,900 --> 00:55:53,714
在你睁开眼睛后 
When you wake up 

919
00:55:53,715 --> 00:55:56,890
你会觉得山姆只是个普通的小伙子
you will think that Sam is just a lad,

920
00:55:56,900 --> 00:55:59,890
跟其他人一样 常常聊天
like all the other lads, plenty of chat,

921
00:55:59,900 --> 00:56:01,900
但你绝对不会嫁给他
but you could never marry him.

922
00:56:08,900 --> 00:56:10,890
我有种奇怪的感觉
I had the strangest feeling.

923
00:56:10,900 --> 00:56:13,890
我...
I...

924
00:56:13,900 --> 00:56:15,890
感觉自己爱上了山姆
I thought I was in love with Sam.

925
00:56:15,900 --> 00:56:17,890
是不是很愚蠢?
Isn't that silly?

926
00:56:17,900 --> 00:56:19,900
要我们转告他你没有吗?
Do we have to tell him that you're not?

927
00:56:29,900 --> 00:56:31,890
我的表又慢了 山姆
It's gone lazy on me again, Sam.

928
00:56:31,900 --> 00:56:33,890
我建议 先生...
May I suggest, sir...

929
00:56:33,900 --> 00:56:35,900
- 修理一下 - 你好 山姆
- Get it fixed. - Hello, Sam.

930
00:56:38,900 --> 00:56:41,890
美食厅取得了巨大的成功
The Food Hall has been a great success.

931
00:56:41,900 --> 00:56:43,890
从来没想过我可能会关心
I had not imagined I might be so engaged by

932
00:56:43,900 --> 00:56:47,890
蛋糕和果子面包怎么能卖得好
by how cakes and buns might sell.

933
00:56:47,900 --> 00:56:50,890
你想今天去参观美食厅吗 芙罗拉?
Would you care to visit the Food Hall today, Flora?

934
00:56:50,900 --> 00:56:52,828
好啊 爸爸 
Yes, Papa. 

935
00:56:52,829 --> 00:56:54,693
想哪时候去? 
What time shall we go? 

936
00:56:54,694 --> 00:56:57,890
今天上午晚点可以吗?
Perhaps later this morning?

937
00:56:57,900 --> 00:56:58,900
好啊
Yes.

938
00:57:34,200 --> 00:57:36,900
巴黎
时尚之都

939
00:57:46,900 --> 00:57:49,900
我发现她坐在我的椅子上 似乎想掌权
I found her sitting in my chair as though she were trying out the throne.

940
00:57:51,900 --> 00:57:53,890
'我再也忍受不了!'
'I cannot bear one more day!'

941
00:57:53,900 --> 00:57:55,395
汤姆会毁了你 
Tom will destroy you. 

942
00:57:55,396 --> 00:57:56,890
德妮丝也会毁了你
Denise will destroy you.

943
00:57:56,900 --> 00:57:58,938
你认为我们应该对抗莫里? 
You think we should defy Moray? 

944
00:57:58,939 --> 00:57:59,890
应该说是帮助
Let's call it helping.

945
00:57:59,900 --> 00:58:01,890
不让他知道的帮助
Without his knowledge or consent.

946
00:58:01,900 --> 00:58:04,900
我认为秘密行动不是最好的方式 德妮丝
'I'm not sure that acting secretly is the best way, Denise.'

